{"type":"message","id":"86aa5e55","parentId":"a6c9b385","timestamp":"2026-05-02T10:38:28.122Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see the issue now. The `minimax-portal` provider doesn't have a `timeoutSeconds` setting configured. Both the \"Emmy Email Check\" and \"Morning Brief\" cron jobs are failing with model idle timeouts because the MiniMax provider has no explicit timeout configured.\n\nThe cron jobs that are failing:\n1. **Emmy Email Check** (d64702cd) - 3 consecutive errors, last error was timeout\n2. **Morning Brief** (0c8b1d5b) - 1 error, also timeout\n\nThe agent-level defaults have `timeoutSeconds: 1200` (20 minutes) at the `agents.defaults` level, but the model provider `minimax-portal` doesn't have its own `timeoutSeconds` setting. The error message says \"The model did not produce a response before the model idle timeout\" - this suggests the model provider-level timeout is what's hitting.\n\n\nI need to add a `timeoutSeconds` configuration to the `minimax-portal` provider. Looking at the schema, the provider doesn't currently have this field set, so I'll need to add it with a reasonable value to prevent the idle timeout errors. the schema, it's likely just a number (in seconds).\n\nLet me add a timeout of 300 seconds (5 minutes) to the minimax-portal provider. That should be enough for email checks and morning briefs.\n\nActually wait - looking at the error more carefully: \"The model did not produce a response before the model idle timeout.\" This seems like it could be a model provider-level idle timeout. Let me check if there's a way to set this on the provider.\n\nI should patch the minimax-portal provider to add a timeoutSeconds setting. I'll use 300 seconds (5 minutes) which should be plenty for most tasks. If that's not enough we can increase it.\n","thinkingSignature":"8b38a696ae47d9934079d1a561f180206bea15681329ac3d4403abf0f70ea092"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nYep — I can see the issue. The **MiniMax provider has no `timeoutSeconds` configured**, and both the **Emmy Email Check** and **Morning Brief** cron jobs are hitting that model idle timeout. The provider-level timeout is likely defaulting to something very short.\n\nLet me add a 300-second timeout to the MiniMax provider:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jg2up22p32vj_1","name":"gateway","arguments":{"action":"config.patch","path":"models.providers.minimax-portal","raw":"{\"timeoutSeconds\": 300}","note":"Added timeoutSeconds: 300 to minimax-portal provider to fix email check and morning brief cron job timeouts."}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":23431,"output":538,"cacheRead":32832,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":56801,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777718296751,"responseId":"064507185312a25951c7555d000cc455"}}
