{"type":"message","id":"904ae786","parentId":"4d89e8ce","timestamp":"2026-05-02T10:41:05.110Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the last email check was at 2:58:35 AM. That's about 3 hours 42 minutes ago (it's currently around 6:40 AM based on the timestamp in the message). The cron job runs every 1 hour, so it should have run several times since then but it's been timing out.\n\nThe timestamp file says 1777705115 which is May 2, 2026 02:58:35 AM EDT.\n\nNow it's about 6:40 AM, so about 3h 42m have passed. The cron should have triggered at:\n- 3:58 AM\n- 4:58 AM\n- 5:58 AM\n- (next would be ~6:58 AM)\n\n\n- \nSo there have definitely been several failures in that window. The timestamp hasn't updated, which means the cron jobs have been timing out before completing. I should manually trigger a check now to see what's happening.\n","thinkingSignature":"6571aca4ec976f0769988161162c477b0b799d4756fef45b32335d4b41146761"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nLast check was **2:58 AM** — so it missed the 3:58, 4:58, and 5:58 AM runs due to the timeouts. Let me run it manually now.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fczvbj85juax_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy && LAST_CHECK=$(cat last_email_check.timestamp 2>/dev/null) && echo \"Last check: $LAST_CHECK\" && echo \"---GMAIL---\" && gog gmail search 'in:inbox is:unread' --max 50 --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com 2>&1","timeout":60}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":140,"output":349,"cacheRead":37056,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":37545,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777718452731,"responseId":"064507b41c6132f8ed0f7cc572ecb8a9"}}
