{"type":"message","id":"b2027461","parentId":"f21ffd0b","timestamp":"2026-05-02T10:41:25.412Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to check which emails arrived after 02:58 AM (timestamp 1777705115). The dates I see from the search aren't directly convertible to Unix timestamps, but the DATE field shows dates like \"2026-05-02 05:01\" which would be after 02:58 AM. Let me get internal dates for the recent emails to filter properly.\n\nActually, the gog gmail search doesn't show the internal Unix timestamp - it shows DATE as a human-readable string. I need to get each email individually to see its internalDate. Let me check the most recent ones.\n\nFrom the search results, the emails from today (May 2) that came after 02:58 AM:\n- 19de7eb7af43961a - 2026-05-02 05:01 - Affirm - statement\n\n\n- 19de6ea8330ae478 - 2026-05-02 00:20 - Apple Music for Artists - this came before 02:58 AM\n\nSo only that Affirm email qualifies as new since May 2 at 05:01 AM. The Apple Music email came in at 00:20 AM, which is too early. Now I should check what's in the iCloud inbox starting from message 10.\n","thinkingSignature":"362ae8c51cfc434ff1d0a3360ee6f9943f13cfb07980f74c8c426cd26721047e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_g7hsugipkzq8_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ICLOUD_CREDS=$(security find-generic-password -a \"rtg.bobby@icloud.com\" -s \"emmy-icloud-email\" -w 2>/dev/null)\ncurl -s --url \"imaps://imap.mail.me.com/INBOX\" --user \"rtg.bobby@icloud.com:$ICLOUD_CREDS\" -X \"SEARCH UNSEEN\" 2>&1","timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":362,"output":381,"cacheRead":40384,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":41127,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777718474429,"responseId":"064507ca67c981b7f0106617e0301c56"}}
