{"type":"message","id":"e70f29bd","parentId":"617f7a03","timestamp":"2026-05-02T10:41:50.790Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"iCloud has no new emails. Now let me filter the Gmail results. The last check was at Unix timestamp 1777705115 (2:58:35 AM). The emails have dates in the format \"2026-05-02\" but I need to convert those to Unix timestamps to compare.\n\nLet me think about which emails came AFTER 2:58:35 AM (timestamp 1777705115):\n- 2026-05-02 05:01 - Affirm - April statement (May 2, 5:01 AM) → AFTER ✓\n- 2026-05-02 00:20 - Apple Music for Artists - Weekly Recap → AFTER ✓\n\n\n- 2026-05-02 (no time listed - probably before 00:20) - Apple - app-specific password generated → AFTER ✓\n\nNow I'm going through the rest to check their timestamps. The X Developer Platform receipt from 11:06 PM on May 1st is also after the cutoff, as is the Y-12 Credit Union statement at 7:12 PM. But the HP.com email at 1:15 PM falls before the 2:58 AM threshold, so that one doesn't qualify.\n\nLooking at the remaining messages, the vidIQ small wins email at 6:08 PM on May 1st is after, while the iHeart Daily newsletter at 5:09 PM is before. I'm continuing through the rest of the list to identify all messages that meet the criteria. more carefully and categorize them by sender and subject.\n\nFor the categorization:\n- **🔴 Bills/Payments** - none really obvious bills, maybe Affirm (but it's just a statement notification)\n- **🟡 Orders** - none\n- **🔵 Updates** - Apple app-specific password generated, Discover Paperless Statements enrolled, Y-12 eStatement available, X Developer Platform receipt\n- **⚪ Low Priority** - Apple Music weekly recap, HP deal, vidIQ, iHeart, TikTok, Netflix, Broadway Direct, ZipRecruiter, PetScreening, etc.\n\nThe most notable ones:\n1. Apple - \"An app-specific password was generated\" - this is a security alert!\n2. Affirm - \"Your April Affirm Card statement is here\" - could be a bill if there's a balance\n3. Discover - \"You're enrolled in Paperless Statements\"\n4. Y-12 Credit Union - \"eStatement is available\"\n5. X Developer Platform - receipt\n\nLet me format this nicely for Bobby.\n\nActually, I should report these in my persona as Emmy. Let me update the timestamp first and then send the report.\n\nHmm, but actually the last timestamp update happens AFTER the report in the cron job prompt. In this case, I should update it after I send the report. But actually I shouldn't update the timestamp until I've truly \"processed\" them - in this manual run, I should update it to prevent duplicates next time.\n\nLet me just send the report and then update the timestamp.\n","thinkingSignature":"445b7f9350dc21893d65019b91f84aad5f0470d85eb032027d512720c30cadfd"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gn3q9487o11s_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"for id in 19de7eb7af43961a 19de6ea8330ae478 19de6a6be8af7a56 19de68d2a9b13ba3 19de5e6b3162ed52; do\n  echo \"=== $id ===\"\n  gog gmail get \"$id\" --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com 2>&1 | grep -E \"^(subject|from|date)\" | head -3\n  echo \"\"\ndone","timeout":60}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":174,"output":759,"cacheRead":40704,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":41637,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777718487049,"responseId":"064507d7c913f3b4ae26fdc491677173"}}
