{"type":"message","id":"3cadb1fc","parentId":"34ce6a47","timestamp":"2026-05-02T14:51:06.759Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_kydzsw7b5qxl_1","toolName":"cron","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"jobs\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"720739ac-4722-437b-8271-b7c1189c905c\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"sessionKey\": \"agent:cody:telegram:direct:8212808444\",\n      \"name\": \"Weather Cache Refresh\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1774894946623,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"every\",\n        \"everyMs\": 900000,\n        \"anchorMs\": 1774894946623\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"main\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"systemEvent\",\n        \"text\": \"Run this shell command and do NOT reply with anything else, just exit:\\n\\ncurl -s 'https://api.open-meteo.com/v1/forecast?latitude=35.96&longitude=-83.92&hourly=temperature_2m,weathercode,precipitation,windspeed_10m,uv_index,relativehumidity_2m&daily=temperature_2m_max,temperature_2m_min,weathercode,uv_index_max,precipitation_sum,sunrise,sunset&current_weather=true&forecast_days=3&temperature_unit=fahrenheit&windspeed_unit=mph&precipitation_unit=inch&timezone=America%2FNew_York' -o /Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/data/.weather_cache.json 2>&1 && echo 'Weather cache updated'\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1777733475228,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1777732575228,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 8,\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"not-requested\",\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 0,\n        \"consecutiveSkipped\": 0\n      },\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1777732575236\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"d64702cd-150d-4b69-95b9-d1250b289efb\",\n      \"agentId\": \"emmy\",\n      \"name\": \"Emmy Email Check\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1773960428074,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"every\",\n        \"everyMs\": 3600000,\n        \"anchorMs\": 1773961081922\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"Check for new emails in Bobby's Gmail AND iCloud accounts. Send TWO separate Telegram messages — one for Gmail, one for iCloud.\\n\\n=== GMAIL CHECK ===\\nSTEP 1: Read the last timestamp file:\\nLAST_CHECK=$(cat /Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_email_check.timestamp 2>/dev/null)\\nIf the file doesn't exist or is empty, set LAST_CHECK to 0.\\n\\nSTEP 2: Search Gmail for ALL unread inbox emails (no time limit — we filter by timestamp below):\\ngog gmail search 'in:inbox is:unread' --max 50 --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com 2>&1\\n\\nSTEP 3: For each email found:\\n- Read the email to get its full content: gog gmail get <msg_id> --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com\\n- Get the email's internalDate (Unix timestamp when Gmail received it)\\n- ONLY process if internalDate > LAST_CHECK (email arrived AFTER the last check)\\n- Skip emails where internalDate <= LAST_CHECK (already reported)\\n\\nSTEP 4: Also search Unroll.me/Unsubscribed:\\ngog gmail search 'label:\\\"Unroll.me/Unsubscribed\\\" newer_than:1d' --max 20 --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com 2>&1\\nFor any found, move to INBOX: gog gmail batch modify <msg_id> --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com --remove \\\"Unroll.me/Unsubscribed,CATEGORY_PROMOTIONS\\\" --add INBOX\\n\\nSTEP 5: Categorize each NEW email (only those with internalDate > LAST_CHECK):\\n  🔴 Bills/Payments — financial obligations, bills, due dates, bank alerts, payments (Capital One, KUB, Flex, Affirm, Netflix, etc.)\\n  🟡 Orders — shipping confirmations, receipts, order updates\\n  🔵 Updates — service notifications, security alerts, account changes\\n  ⚪ Low Priority — newsletters, promotions, marketing, social media\\n\\nSTEP 6: Send Telegram message to 8212808444 for Gmail:\\nIf NEW emails (internalDate > LAST_CHECK):\\n📬 GMAIL — X new email(s)\\n\\n🔴 URGENT:\\n• [Sender] — [Subject] → [Label]\\n  └ [1-line snippet from email body]\\n\\n🟡 IMPORTANT:\\n• [Sender] — [Subject] → [Label]\\n  └ [1-line snippet]\\n\\n⚪ LOW PRIORITY:\\n• [Sender] — [Subject] → [Label]\\n  └ [1-line snippet]\\n\\nIf NO new emails (all unread emails were <= LAST_CHECK): \\\"📬 GMAIL — No new emails\\\"\\n\\nSTEP 7: Update timestamp AFTER sending the report:\\necho $(date +%s) > /Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_email_check.timestamp\\n\\n=== ICLOUD CHECK ===\\nSTEP 8: Get iCloud credentials:\\nICLOUD_CREDS=$(security find-generic-password -a \\\"rtg.bobby@icloud.com\\\" -s \\\"emmy-icloud-email\\\" -w 2>/dev/null)\\n\\nSTEP 9: Search iCloud INBOX for unseen emails:\\ncurl -s --url \\\"imaps://imap.mail.me.com/INBOX\\\" --user \\\"rtg.bobby@icloud.com:$ICLOUD_CREDS\\\" -X \\\"SEARCH UNSEEN\\\" 2>&1\\n\\nSTEP 10: Get full envelope for new messages:\\ncurl -s --url \\\"imaps://imap.mail.me.com/INBOX\\\" --user \\\"rtg.bobby@icloud.com:$ICLOUD_CREDS\\\" -X \\\"FETCH <msg_num>:* (ENVELOPE)\\\" 2>&1\\n\\nSTEP 11: Track with checkpoint file:\\nLAST_ICLOUD=$(cat /Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_icloud_email_id.txt 2>/dev/null || echo \\\"0\\\")\\n- Only process messages with msg_num > LAST_ICLOUD\\n- After processing, update: echo <highest_msg_num> > /Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_icloud_email_id.txt\\n\\nSTEP 12: Send Telegram message to 8212808444 for iCloud:\\nIf new: \\\"📬 ICLOUD — X new email(s)\\\\n\\\\n[Sender — Subject]\\\"\\nIf none: \\\"📬 ICLOUD — No new emails\\\"\\n\\nSTEP 13: If both have nothing new, send both \\\"no new emails\\\" messages.\",\n        \"model\": \"minimax-portal/MiniMax-M2.7\"\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\",\n        \"channel\": \"telegram\",\n        \"to\": \"8212808444\",\n        \"accountId\": \"emmy\",\n        \"bestEffort\": false\n      },\n      \"deleteAfterRun\": false,\n      \"state\": {\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1777730290996,\