  \"nextOffset\": null,\n  \"deliveryPreviews\": {\n    \"720739ac-4722-437b-8271-b7c1189c905c\": {\n      \"label\": \"not requested\",\n      \"detail\": \"not requested\"\n    },\n    \"d64702cd-150d-4b69-95b9-d1250b289efb\": {\n      \"label\": \"announce -> telegram:8212808444\",\n      \"detail\": \"explicit\"\n    },\n    \"ecc194aa-784b-4fd8-bb18-7088d1077903\": {\n      \"label\": \"none -> telegram:8212808444\",\n      \"detail\": \"explicit\"\n    },\n    \"3f20d0fb-bb39-4216-a3a2-d87613e075f4\": {\n      \"label\": \"none -> last\",\n      \"detail\": \"last -> no route, will fail-closed: Delivering to Telegram requires target <chatId>\"\n    },\n    \"6c87956b-dd85-4e4e-8f7d-6c9384c9f9d7\": {\n      \"label\": \"announce -> telegram:8212808444\",\n      \"detail\": \"explicit\"\n    },\n    \"e63a926f-487e-4bbc-a626-cbf21b1b8670\": {\n      \"label\": \"none -> telegram:telegram:8212808444\",\n      \"detail\": \"resolved from last, session agent:main:telegram:direct:8212808444\"\n    },\n    \"0c8b1d5b-b2fd-45d4-b346-517699a1e000\": {\n      \"label\": \"announce -> telegram:8212808444\",\n      \"detail\": \"explicit\"\n    },\n    \"295537b1-3a90-436f-b7de-67d69a5347db\": {\n      \"label\": \"none -> telegram:8212808444\",\n      \"detail\": \"explicit\"\n    },\n    \"d0c43bd5-ad9a-4911-b0a9-81b9e4a1e30c\": {\n      \"label\": \"announce -> telegram:8212808444\",\n      \"detail\": \"explicit\"\n    },\n    \"23feb105-d412-4a3f-b94a-5ff8cb0abcc5\": {\n      \"label\": \"none -> telegram:8212808444\",\n      \"detail\": \"explicit\"\n    }\n  }\n}[... 642 more characters truncated]"}],"details":{"persistedDetailsTruncated":true,"originalDetailsBytesAtLeast":8193,"originalDetailKeys":["jobs","total","offset","limit","hasMore","nextOffset","deliveryPreviews"],"total":10},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777733466758}}
{"type":"message","id":"a02e484f","parentId":"3cadb1fc","timestamp":"2026-05-02T14:51:18.912Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the full email check cron job. It ran successfully after the restart - lastRunStatus is \"ok\" and lastDurationMs is 295346 (about 5 minutes). But it took almost 5 minutes because of the context loading.\n\nThe main issue is that the prompt is extremely long and detailed - it's basically asking the model to act like a script executor, doing step-by-step shell commands. The model has to:\n1. Load all workspace context files\n2. Interpret the long prompt\n3. Execute step-by-step instructions with external tool calls\n4. Compose the response\n\nFor an isolated session, it also loads the workspace context which includes SOUL.md, USER.md, MEMORY.md, etc.\n\n\nThe prompt itself is what needs optimization - it's running through all these email checks and categorizations when it could be streamlined to just pull new emails since the last run and send a quick summary. Instead of the model interpreting and executing each step, I could simplify this significantly.\n","thinkingSignature":"885fa8a3a832aade0b6b9f18bbe12955f140068c1825a865fa34c3e3a79807ae"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nHere's the full prompt the **Emmy Email Check** cron job runs every hour:\n\n```\nCheck for new emails in Bobby's Gmail AND iCloud accounts. Send TWO separate Telegram messages — one for Gmail, one for iCloud.\n\n=== GMAIL CHECK ===\nSTEP 1: Read the last timestamp file:\nLAST_CHECK=$(cat /Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_email_check.timestamp 2>/dev/null)\nIf the file doesn't exist or is empty, set LAST_CHECK to 0.\nSTEP 2: Search Gmail for ALL unread inbox emails...\n[... 20+ more steps ...]\n```\n\n**The problem I see:**\n\nIt's written as a step-by-step shell script the model has to interpret and execute — 13 steps for Gmail + iCloud. The model spends most of its time:\n1. **Loading workspace context** (~50K+ tokens from SOUL.md, USER.md, MEMORY.md, etc.)\n2. **Parsing the long prompt** and figuring out what to do\n3. **Making individual exec calls** for each step\n\nThen it hits the timeout before it can finish everything and send the message.\n\n**What I recommend — simplify the prompt** to be more direct, like:\n- \"Check Gmail/iCloud for unread emails since [last timestamp]. Send a concise summary to Telegram 8212808444. Use gog for Gmail, curl for iCloud.\"\n\nWant me to update the cron job with a leaner prompt that cuts the step-by-step overhead? It should finish well within the timeout."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":5197,"output":522,"cacheRead":45280,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":50999,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777733466760,"responseId":"0645425ad84dd69fc1569e80d579a88e"}}
