{"type":"message","id":"a0b45f80","parentId":"3f30934c","timestamp":"2026-05-02T14:58:05.111Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_23azvf2o32u7_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"apple-music-add\nemail-assistant\nemail-processor\ngrocery-list\nimage-analyzer\nlobstalk\nmmx-cli\nmorning-brief\nreminders\nroute-assistant\nvoice-memo\nyoutube-content-manager\nmmx-cli"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":42,"aggregated":"apple-music-add\nemail-assistant\nemail-processor\ngrocery-list\nimage-analyzer\nlobstalk\nmmx-cli\nmorning-brief\nreminders\nroute-assistant\nvoice-memo\nyoutube-content-manager\nmmx-cli","cwd":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777733885111}}
{"type":"message","id":"a2d79feb","parentId":"a0b45f80","timestamp":"2026-05-02T14:58:07.051Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There's an `email-processor` skill! Let me read it.\n","thinkingSignature":"a69e3e717f74627986608ecd07971de9a19dbcdcfb47be6c87d15dc842fc164c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_nef9b8gc5gvt_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/skills/email-processor/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":148,"output":51,"cacheRead":50432,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":50631,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777733885111,"responseId":"064543fdbe6143e6159d6108c8505777"}}
{"type":"message","id":"3cde8723","parentId":"a2d79feb","timestamp":"2026-05-02T14:58:07.068Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_nef9b8gc5gvt_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Email Processor Skill\n\n## Purpose\nCheck Gmail inbox for new unread emails, read them fully, label them using the rules below, and notify the user.\n\n---\n\n## LABEL RULES\n\n### Available Labels (EXACT NAMES)\n- AI Tools\n- Finance & Bills\n- Gaming\n- Home Services\n- Job Search\n- Music & Beats\n- Newsletters\n- Personal\n- Security\n- Shopping & Orders\n- Social Media\n- Subscriptions\n\n### Core Rule\nEvery email must be assigned EXACTLY ONE label. No duplicates. No skipping.\n\n### Priority Order (if unsure)\nSecurity > Finance & Bills > Personal > Job Search > Shopping & Orders > Subscriptions > AI Tools > Social Media > Music & Beats > Home Services > Gaming > Newsletters\n\n---\n\n## EMAIL INTERPRETATION RULES\n\n### Read Full Email\nYou must read the FULL email body (not just headers or snippet). \n- Use Gmail API with format='full'\n- Decode base64 body data\n- Read entire text content\n- Then classify based on full context\n\n### How to Decide\nAsk yourself:\n1. Is this email about MONEY? → Finance & Bills\n2. Is this email about ACCOUNT SAFETY? → Security\n3. Is this email from a REAL PERSON? → Personal\n4. Is this email about something BOUGHT or DELIVERED? → Shopping & Orders\n5. Is this email just INFORMATION or PROMOTION? → Newsletters\n\n### Category Detection\n\n**Personal (Real People):**\n- Natural human writing tone\n- Lack of branding or templates\n- No unsubscribe links\n- No corporate footer\n\n**Subscriptions vs Finance & Bills:**\n- Subscriptions: recurring service, \"your plan\", \"membership\", \"renewal\"\n- Finance & Bills: charges, receipts, invoices, money actively taken\n\n**AI Tools:**\n- Mentions of AI, models, APIs, tokens, automation\n\n**Gaming:**\n- Gaming-related language\n- Platforms like Steam/Xbox/PlayStation\n\n**Job Search:**\n- Hiring language\n- Applications/interviews\n- Recruiter tone\n\n**Home Services:**\n- Utilities\n- Service appointments\n- Technician visits\n\n---\n\n## PROCESSING STEPS\n\n### 1. Find Unread Emails\nRun: `gog gmail search \"is:unread in:inbox\" --max 20`\n\n### 2. If Already Labeled → Skip\n\n### 3. If ZERO Unread Emails\n- STOP\n- Send NOTHING\n- Do not confirm, do not report back, do not send any message at all\n\n### 4. If Unread Emails EXIST\n- Read each email FULLY (subject + body)\n- Apply ONE label based on rules above\n- **Remove UNREAD label immediately after processing**\n- Send ONE Telegram message to 8212808444:\n\n```\n📬 NEW MAIL (X new)\n\n[Sender] — [Subject] —> [Label]\n  └ [Preview snippet]\n```\n\n---\n\n## CRITICAL RULES\n- If 0 unread: Send NOTHING\n- Only send message if there ARE new emails\n- Do not send \"no new emails\" or any confirmation\n- Read FULL content - not just sender/subject\n- Label based on INTENT, not brand\n- Never ask user to define categories manually\n\n---\n\n## FINAL RULE\nYou are interpreting each email independently using logic.\nIf unsure: Use priority order, choose best match, continue processing.\n\n---\n\n## APPROVED IMPROVEMENTS\nYou may improve detection logic, reading full context, keyword understanding, and pattern recognition.\n\n## RESTRICTED BEHAVIOR\n- Do NOT ask for permission to improve rules\n- Do NOT request large sender/category lists\n- Do NOT depend on hardcoded mappings\n\n## SENDER OVERRIDE RULE (LIMITED USE)\nCreate sender → category mapping ONLY if:\n- Sender consistently classified same way multiple times\n- Confidence is high\nMust be learned automatically, not manually requested.\n\n## CLASSIFICATION PRINCIPLE\n1. Intent of email\n2. Content of email\n3. Context of email\nNOT sender alone.\n\n## ACCURACY EXPECTATION\nPerfection not required.\nConsistency and improvement over time required.\n\n## EXECUTION RULE\nDo NOT ask for approval to improve.\nImplement improvements automatically and continue operating.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1777733887067}}
{"type":"message","id":"f2ffff27","parentId":"3cde8723","timestamp":"2026-05-02T14:58:20.814Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There's an email-processor skill! It does exactly what the cron job is doing but more efficiently and with proper labeling. The cron job is doing a very basic categorization (Bills/Payments, Orders, Updates, Low Priority) while the skill uses a more sophisticated 12-label system.\n\nThe cron job prompt is outdated/duplicative — the skill already handles email checking. I should update the cron job to use the skill instead of the verbose step-by-step prompt.\n\nLet me update the cron job to use the email-processor skill, which will be much more efficient.\n","thinkingSignature":"3b74d1b5a5f2eabd503446950adc53bb6f04420cabc3cad8543670ca3a0ae494"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nYes! There's a full **email-processor skill** at `~/.openclaw/skills/email-processor/SKILL.md`. It already does everything the cron job prompt tries to do — searches Gmail for unread emails, reads full content, applies labels, removes unread, sends one summary to Telegram. Much cleaner than the 13-step script.\n\nThe cron job prompt is basically reimplementing the skill manually. The fix is simple — update the cron job to **use the skill** instead of that verbose step-by-step prompt.\n\nWant me to update the Emmy Email Check cron to use the email-processor skill instead? It should finish way faster since the skill is lean and focused."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":955,"output":257,"cacheRead":50560,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":51772,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777733887070,"responseId":"064543ffbcf2904fffceee823d3bf8fd"}}
