{"type":"message","id":"3aa5013b","parentId":"ec09cf7d","timestamp":"2026-05-02T15:00:16.148Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_0ppj3ph2bg9r_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Email Processor Skill\n\n## Purpose\nCheck Gmail inbox for new unread emails, read them fully, label them using the rules below, and notify the user.\n\n---\n\n## LABEL RULES\n\n### Available Labels (EXACT NAMES)\n- AI Tools\n- Finance & Bills\n- Gaming\n- Home Services\n- Job Search\n- Music & Beats\n- Newsletters\n- Personal\n- Security\n- Shopping & Orders\n- Social Media\n- Subscriptions\n\n### Core Rule\nEvery email must be assigned EXACTLY ONE label. No duplicates. No skipping.\n\n### Priority Order (if unsure)\nSecurity > Finance & Bills > Personal > Job Search > Shopping & Orders > Subscriptions > AI Tools > Social Media > Music & Beats > Home Services > Gaming > Newsletters\n\n---\n\n## EMAIL INTERPRETATION RULES\n\n### Read Full Email\nYou must read the FULL email body (not just headers or snippet). \n- Use Gmail API with format='full'\n- Decode base64 body data\n- Read entire text content\n- Then classify based on full context\n\n### How to Decide\nAsk yourself:\n1. Is this email about MONEY? → Finance & Bills\n2. Is this email about ACCOUNT SAFETY? → Security\n3. Is this email from a REAL PERSON? → Personal\n4. Is this email about something BOUGHT or DELIVERED? → Shopping & Orders\n5. Is this email just INFORMATION or PROMOTION? → Newsletters\n\n### Category Detection\n\n**Personal (Real People):**\n- Natural human writing tone\n- Lack of branding or templates\n- No unsubscribe links\n- No corporate footer\n\n**Subscriptions vs Finance & Bills:**\n- Subscriptions: recurring service, \"your plan\", \"membership\", \"renewal\"\n- Finance & Bills: charges, receipts, invoices, money actively taken\n\n**AI Tools:**\n- Mentions of AI, models, APIs, tokens, automation\n\n**Gaming:**\n- Gaming-related language\n- Platforms like Steam/Xbox/PlayStation\n\n**Job Search:**\n- Hiring language\n- Applications/interviews\n- Recruiter tone\n\n**Home Services:**\n- Utilities\n- Service appointments\n- Technician visits\n\n---\n\n## PROCESSING STEPS\n\n### 1. Find Unread Emails\nRun: `gog gmail search \"is:unread in:inbox\" --max 20`\n\n### 2. If Already Labeled → Skip\n\n### 3. If ZERO Unread Emails\n- STOP\n- Send NOTHING\n- Do not confirm, do not report back, do not send any message at all\n\n### 4. If Unread Emails EXIST\n- Read each email FULLY (subject + body)\n- Apply ONE label based on rules above\n- **Remove UNREAD label immediately after processing**\n- Send ONE Telegram message to 8212808444:\n\n```\n📬 NEW MAIL (X new)\n\n[Sender] — [Subject] —> [Label]\n  └ [Preview snippet]\n```\n\n---\n\n## CRITICAL RULES\n- If 0 unread: Send NOTHING\n- Only send message if there ARE new emails\n- Do not send \"no new emails\" or any confirmation\n- Read FULL content - not just sender/subject\n- Label based on INTENT, not brand\n- Never ask user to define categories manually\n\n---\n\n## FINAL RULE\nYou are interpreting each email independently using logic.\nIf unsure: Use priority order, choose best match, continue processing.\n\n---\n\n## APPROVED IMPROVEMENTS\nYou may improve detection logic, reading full context, keyword understanding, and pattern recognition.\n\n## RESTRICTED BEHAVIOR\n- Do NOT ask for permission to improve rules\n- Do NOT request large sender/category lists\n- Do NOT depend on hardcoded mappings\n\n## SENDER OVERRIDE RULE (LIMITED USE)\nCreate sender → category mapping ONLY if:\n- Sender consistently classified same way multiple times\n- Confidence is high\nMust be learned automatically, not manually requested.\n\n## CLASSIFICATION PRINCIPLE\n1. Intent of email\n2. Content of email\n3. Context of email\nNOT sender alone.\n\n## ACCURACY EXPECTATION\nPerfection not required.\nConsistency and improvement over time required.\n\n## EXECUTION RULE\nDo NOT ask for approval to improve.\nImplement improvements automatically and continue operating.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1777734016148}}
{"type":"message","id":"2e4c2e4a","parentId":"3aa5013b","timestamp":"2026-05-02T15:00:45.922Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to update the skill to include both Gmail AND iCloud email accounts. Let me rewrite the SKILL.md to cover both accounts.","thinkingSignature":"54dc555974d43ffd5b3cda934c670b7ee1ec7ce212d5731d84624f42513d5b81"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_t3fwsgrvz8we_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# Email Processor Skill\n\n## Purpose\nCheck **Gmail** and **iCloud** inboxes for new unread emails, read them fully, label them using the rules below, and notify the user via Telegram — with **separate messages** for each account.\n\n---\n\n## LABEL RULES\n\n### Available Labels (EXACT NAMES)\n- AI Tools\n- Finance & Bills\n- Gaming\n- Home Services\n- Job Search\n- Music & Beats\n- Newsletters\n- Personal\n- Security\n- Shopping & Orders\n- Social Media\n- Subscriptions\n\n### Core Rule\nEvery email must be assigned EXACTLY ONE label. No duplicates. No skipping.\n\n### Priority Order (if unsure)\nSecurity > Finance & Bills > Personal > Job Search > Shopping & Orders > Subscriptions > AI Tools > Social Media > Music & Beats > Home Services > Gaming > Newsletters\n\n---\n\n## EMAIL INTERPRETATION RULES\n\n### Gmail\n- Use `gog gmail search \"is:unread in:inbox\" --max 20 --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com`\n- Read full content: `gog gmail get <msg_id> --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com`\n- After processing, mark as read: `gog gmail batch modify <msg_id> --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com --remove UNREAD`\n\n### iCloud\n- Credentials: `ICLOUD_CREDS=$(security find-generic-password -a \"rtg.bobby@icloud.com\" -s \"emmy-icloud-email\" -w 2>/dev/null)`\n- Search for unseen: `curl -s --url \"imaps://imap.mail.me.com/INBOX\" --user \"rtg.bobby@icloud.com:$ICLOUD_CREDS\" -X \"SEARCH UNSEEN\" 2>&1`\n- Fetch envelope: `curl -s --url \"imaps://imap.mail.me.com/INBOX\" --user \"rtg.bobby@icloud.com:$ICLOUD_CREDS\" -X \"FETCH <msg_num>:* (ENVELOPE)\" 2>&1`\n- Track with checkpoint file `last_icloud_email_id.txt` — only process msgs with msg_num > checkpoint, then update checkpoint\n\n### How to Decide\n1. Is this email about MONEY? → Finance & Bills\n2. Is this email about ACCOUNT SAFETY? → Security\n3. Is this email from a REAL PERSON? → Personal\n4. Is this email about something BOUGHT or DELIVERED? → Shopping & Orders\n5. Is this email just INFORMATION or PROMOTION? → Newsletters\n\n### Category Detection\n\n**Personal (Real People):**\n- Natural human writing tone\n- Lack of branding or templates\n- No unsubscribe links\n- No corporate footer\n\n**Subscriptions vs Finance & Bills:**\n- Subscriptions: recurring service, \"your plan\", \"membership\", \"renewal\"\n- Finance & Bills: charges, receipts, invoices, money actively taken\n\n**AI Tools:**\n- Mentions of AI, models, APIs, tokens, automation\n\n**Gaming:**\n- Gaming-related language, platforms like Steam/Xbox/PlayStation\n\n**Job Search:**\n- Hiring language, applications/interviews, recruiter tone\n\n**Home Services:**\n- Utilities, service appointments, technician visits\n\n---\n\n## PROCESSING STEPS\n\n### GMAIL CHECK\n\n1. Get last timestamp: `cat last_email_check.timestamp` (Unix epoch). If missing/invalid, use 0.\n2. Search unread inbox: `gog gmail search \"is:unread in:inbox\" --max 50 --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com`\n3. For each email, read full content and check internalDate — skip if <= last timestamp (already processed)\n4. Also check Unroll.me/Unsubscribed and move back to INBOX if found\n5. Label each new email, then mark read\n6. Send **one Gmail Telegram message** to 8212808444 (or skip if 0 new)\n7. Update timestamp: `echo $(date +%s) > last_email_check.timestamp`\n\n### ICLOUD CHECK\n\n1. Get credentials from keychain\n2. Search UNSEEN in INBOX\n3. Compare msg numbers against `last_icloud_email_id.txt` checkpoint\n4. Only process messages with msg_num > checkpoint\n5. Fetch full envelope for each new message\n6. Send **one iCloud Telegram message** to 8212808444 (or skip if 0 new)\n7. Update checkpoint: `echo <highest_msg_num> > last_icloud_email_id.txt`\n\n---\n\n## MESSAGE FORMAT\n\n### Gmail — new emails found:\n```\n📬 GMAIL — X new email(s)\n\n🔴 URGENT:\n• [Sender] — [Subject] —> [Label]\n  └ [Preview snippet]\n\n🟡 IMPORTANT:\n• [Sender] — [Subject] —> [Label]\n  └ [Preview snippet]\n\n⚪ LOW PRIORITY:\n• [Sender] — [Subject] —> [Label]\n  └ [Preview snippet]\n```\n\nIf no new emails: `📬 GMAIL — No new emails`\n\n### iCloud — new emails found:\n```\n📬 ICLOUD — X new email(s)\n\n• [Sender] — [Subject]\n```\n\nIf no new emails: `📬 ICLOUD — No new emails`\n\n---\n\n## CRITICAL RULES\n- If 0 unread from an account: send \"No new emails\" for that account only\n- Always send separate messages for Gmail and iCloud\n- Read FULL content — not just headers or snippets\n- Label based on INTENT, not brand\n- Never ask user to define categories\n- Update timestamps/checkpoints AFTER sending each report\n\n---\n\n## APPROVED IMPROVEMENTS\nYou may improve detection logic, reading full context, keyword understanding, and pattern recognition.\n\n## RESTRICTED BEHAVIOR\n- Do NOT ask for permission to improve rules\n- Do NOT request large sender/category lists\n- Do NOT depend on hardcoded mappings\n\n## SENDER OVERRIDE RULE (LIMITED USE)\nCreate sender → category mapping ONLY if sender consistently classified same way multiple times with high confidence. Must be learned automatically.\n\n## CLASSIFICATION PRINCIPLE\n1. Intent of email\n2. Content of email\n3. Context of email\nNOT sender alone.\n\n## ACCURACY EXPECTATION\nPerfection not required. Consistency and improvement over time required.\n\n## EXECUTION RULE\nDo NOT ask for approval to improve. Implement improvements automatically and continue operating.\n","path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/skills/email-processor/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":970,"output":1431,"cacheRead":51776,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":54177,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777734016149,"responseId":"06454480112bfa6828e4c3d59ac5dbf9"}}
