{"type":"message","id":"55cb00f1","parentId":"dc8a2262","timestamp":"2026-05-02T15:02:28.363Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby is asking if the email skill has the message format for how to send the emails to him. Let me check - yes, the skill does have message format sections (GMAIL MESSAGE FORMAT and ICLOUD MESSAGE FORMAT) that specify how to format the emails when sending to Telegram. Let me confirm this.","thinkingSignature":"d48be64b68d5b643a2b3bc901cc61280b302a5afb0525765ac47f0d3ad3bf333"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\nYes! The skill has it. Here's the format it uses:\n\n**For Gmail:**\n```\n📬 GMAIL — X new email(s)\n\n🔴 URGENT:\n• [Sender] — [Subject] —> [Label]\n  └ [Preview snippet]\n\n🟡 IMPORTANT:\n• [Sender] — [Subject] —> [Label]\n  └ [Preview snippet]\n\n⚪ LOW PRIORITY:\n• [Sender] — [Subject] —> [Label]\n  └ [Preview snippet]\n```\n\nIf no new emails: `📬 GMAIL — No new emails`\n\n**For iCloud:**\n```\n📬 ICLOUD — X new email(s)\n\n• [Sender] — [Subject]\n```\n\nIf no new emails: `📬 ICLOUD — No new emails`\n\nSame style you had with the old cron job — separate Gmail and iCloud messages, organized by priority."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":59712,"output":246,"cacheRead":224,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":60182,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777734124966,"responseId":"064544ed688cfa3f2f65173204cd38b2"}}
