{"type":"message","id":"cd00ca1a","parentId":"0bcde550","timestamp":"2026-05-02T15:05:12.762Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the default agent timeout is 1200 seconds (20 minutes). But the cron job payload itself has `timeoutSeconds: 300` (5 minutes) set explicitly. Let me check what the actual provider-level timeout is for MiniMax. It seems there's no `timeoutSeconds` set at the provider level, so it probably defaults to something.\n\nActually, the cron job has `timeoutSeconds: 300` in its payload - that's set on the job itself. The model provider timeout would be separate. The error message says \"model idle timeout\" which is different from the provider HTTP timeout.\n\nLet me check what the actual idle timeout is. It might be a system default.\n","thinkingSignature":"daf6b7fe4170994e241f3b339508bd35201e29112438090d4b3e521f4fa5f858"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_yeo0rxnowrlz_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw config get --json 2>&1 | grep -i \"idle\\|timeout\" | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":183,"output":184,"cacheRead":60672,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":61039,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777734304692,"responseId":"064545a044779c5542c5e1b1a8423029"}}
