{"type":"message","id":"6564e607","parentId":"2864b963","timestamp":"2026-05-02T15:19:05.516Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The last run of the Emmy Email Check cron was STILL the old prompt that timed out. My update to the cron job happened AFTER that run. Let me confirm the current cron job message is the new one:\n\nCurrent cron job message: \"Run the email processor skill at ~/.openclaw/skills/email-processor/SKILL.md. Follow it exactly. Send Gmail results and iCloud results as separate Telegram messages to 8212808444.\"\n\nThe lastRunAtMs was 1777733891009 and the error happened at 1777734224999. My update was at 1777734054775. So the error occurred at 1777734224999 which is after my update at 1777734054775. Wait, that means the cron that errored ran AFTER my update!\n \nActually, I need to recalculate the timeline more carefully. The error occurred at 1777734224999, but I applied the update at 1777734054775, so the cron that failed was the one I just modified. And its duration was 333990ms, which is about 5.5 minutes—that's longer than the 300 second timeout I set.\n\nBut here's what's odd: the last successful run was at 1777730290996 with a duration of 295346ms (~4.9 min), which didn't timeout. The failed run at 1777733891009 ran for 333990ms (~5.56 min) and did timeout. The timeout I set was 300 seconds, so this makes sense—the job exceeded the timeout.\n\nActually wait, I need to reconsider the order. The job ran at 1777733891009 and errored with a timeout at 1777734224999, which means the job started AFTER my last update at 1777734054775. My update to the cron job message happened at 1777734054775, so this was definitely the new version that timed out. It looks like the model is taking longer than the 300-second timeout allows.\n\nThe core issue seems to be that even with the simpler skill prompt, the model is still timing out at around 5.5 minutes. This could be a MiniMax availability or latency issue, so I should probably suggest Bobby try a different model for this job.\n","thinkingSignature":"9c0ae8f31350733e5058ce13b6f6603095304b5d67609aab66a8321a32b49160"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nHere's what the **Emmy Email Check** cron job says now:\n\n```\nRun the email processor skill at ~/.openclaw/skills/email-processor/SKILL.md. \nFollow it exactly. Send Gmail results and iCloud results as separate Telegram messages to 8212808444.\n\nModel: minimax-portal/MiniMax-M2.7\ntimeoutSeconds: 300\nSchedule: every 1 hour\nSession: isolated\n```\n\nThat's the updated version I set — clean and simple.\n\n**But here's the problem:** It STILL timed out. The last run after my update took **~5.56 min (333,990ms)** before hitting the idle timeout. That run was using my new lean prompt but still exceeded the threshold.\n\nThe model itself is taking longer than expected to process even the streamlined skill. The idle timeout appears to be around 5-5.5 minutes and MiniMax M2.7 is consistently hitting or exceeding that.\n\n**Options to fix:**\n1. **Switch to Grok 4.1 Fast** — it's already configured and should be much faster for this straightforward task\n2. **Accept the current timing** — it works sometimes (4.9 min success) but fails when MiniMax is slower\n\nWant me to update the cron to use Grok 4.1 Fast instead?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":4354,"output":741,"cacheRead":63616,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":68711,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777735121520,"responseId":"064548d1f0e65e81fb5bf3dfdba8246c"}}
