{"type":"message","id":"007203bd","parentId":"2cbad15f","timestamp":"2026-05-02T15:22:27.433Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby's frustrated - the old cron job was actually working fine! Let me look at the cron job state history more carefully.\n\nFrom the cron list:\n- lastRunStatus: \"ok\" at lastRunAtMs: 1777730290996, durationMs: 295346 (~4.9 min)\n- But then it shows an error at 1777733891009 with durationMs: 333990 (~5.56 min) - THAT was a timeout\n\nWait, let me look at this more carefully. The state shows:\n1. First: lastRunAtMs: 1777730290996, lastRunStatus: \"ok\", lastDurationMs: 295346\n\n\n2. Then after my patch: runningAtMs: 1777733891009 and that's when the timeout happened\n\nSo the pattern is clear: the original email check cron was actually succeeding with a ~4.9 minute runtime, but after I modified it, it started timing out at ~5.5 minutes. I replaced the working 13-step prompt with my new skill-based approach and that broke it.\n\nThe timeout error suggests MiniMax M2.7 is now struggling with the skill's longer context, which is the real problem I need to focus on solving. The context loading and parsing is taking too long.\n\nSo the real issue is that I should keep the old working prompt as the base and just incorporate the skill-based approach as an optimization, not a complete rewrite.\n","thinkingSignature":"f181d82c5cdb76391a20d7cf0e047d2a7c71fdc7927fc0d7dc67f2ae6ce4bbc0"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nYou're right, I messed up. Let me look back at the history more carefully:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_orksx30z3imi_1","name":"cron","arguments":{"action":"runs","jobId":"d64702cd-150d-4b69-95b9-d1250b289efb"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":68053,"output":372,"cacheRead":352,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":68777,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777735273