{"type":"message","id":"93ec44aa","parentId":"52f116e8","timestamp":"2026-05-02T15:25:26.362Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby is asking a straightforward clarification question. The cron job is the automated hourly check, and the skill is the email-processor skill file. We just reverted the cron job to use the old 13-step script prompt, NOT the skill. But the skill is also updated with iCloud support and the urgency format.\n\nSo currently:\n- The **cron job** uses the old 13-step script (not the skill)\n- The **skill** is a standalone file that has the enhanced format with iCloud + urgency labels, which could be used manually or in the future\n\nBobby wants to know which one we're using. I should clarify that the cron job is using the old script, but the skill is a better option that we should probably migrate to. Let me also clarify the iCloud format question - the cron job still uses the old format for iCloud (no urgency categories), while the skill has the updated iCloud format.\n \nThe cron job is set up to run the old 13-step script, but the skill file has all the improvements we made - iCloud support and the better urgency categorization format. The cron job isn't actually invoking the skill yet, so we're using the script for automation while the skill sits ready as a better alternative we could switch to.\n","thinkingSignature":"6c392eece7065e528e1b69bc21e40a50940ad2c05373fb8e35b44578eb57e373"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nRight now:\n\n- **Cron job** → uses the old 13-step script (not the skill)\n- **Skill** → `email-processor/SKILL.md` with the enhanced iCloud + urgency format, ready to use\n\nThe skill is better — it has proper urgent/important/low priority formatting for BOTH Gmail and iCloud, plus cleaner label rules. The cron job is still on the old script because I just reverted it to what was proven to work.\n\nTwo options going forward:\n\n1. **Keep the cron on the old script** — reliable, proven, but iCloud messages won't have the urgency categories (just flat list)\n2. **Update the cron to use the skill** — better formatting for both accounts, but we saw it timeout on the lean prompt\n\nWhich do you want to go with? If you want the skill format for iCloud too, we should probably test it on the next cron run first before committing."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":75991,"output":450,"cacheRead":128,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":76569,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777735508239,"responseId":"06454a5954efd65fa452366464b35fc1"}}
