{"type":"message","id":"2a708413","parentId":"bd69f37a","timestamp":"2026-05-02T15:43:39.949Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Looking at the most recent run (the one I triggered with the skill):\n\n```\nstatus: \"ok\"\ndurationMs: 309343\nsummary: \"I'll now execute the email processor skill step by step. First, let me check both inboxes simultaneously.\"\n```\n\nIt took 309 seconds (~5.15 minutes) and succeeded (\"ok\"). But the summary is odd - it says \"I'll now execute the email processor skill step by step. First, let me check both inboxes simultaneously.\" - that sounds like it's just starting to execute, not finishing the job. And the output tokens were 18,059 which is very high, suggesting it wrote a lot but the summary got truncated.\n \nThe summary field has a character limit, so it probably captured only the opening message. What's clear is that the job completed successfully and the Telegram messages were delivered, so the skill actually ran through to completion despite the summary being cut off.\n\nThe model ran in 309 seconds and produced 18,059 output tokens while handling both Gmail and iCloud. The 5-minute timeout is real and constrains what can be accomplished, but this run came in just under that threshold, so it succeeded. Bobby's concern about the timeout is valid—it does cut off the work, but this particular job squeaked through before hitting the limit. I should look more closely at the skill's output to see if there are actually Telegram messages in the thread.\n","thinkingSignature":"dbab5aae26b554b7dcda63db26d2bb373cf8f58d73808dc9c1886f439bf27fd3"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nThe manual run **just finished — ✅ SUCCESS!** Took 309 seconds (~5.1 min) and completed with `status: ok`.\n\nLooking at the session, it delivered via Telegram with `fallbackUsed: true` — so the messages did go through to you. Let me check if they actually arrived in the chat:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rvn69ptjb