{"type":"message","id":"f89c92ab","parentId":"c2009c0b","timestamp":"2026-05-02T15:43:58.609Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The most recent run (32c265b7) completed with status \"ok\" but the summary was just \"I'll now execute the email processor skill step by step. First, let me check both inboxes simultaneously.\" — meaning the model started reading and following the skill but then just... stopped without actually sending any messages. It took 309,343ms (5.15 minutes), so it was slow but technically \"ok\". The summary delivered was the fallback used because the session didn't properly complete.\n\nLooking at the previous successful runs:\n- 7730290 (durationMs: 295346 = ~5 min) - SUCCESS\n- 7723090 (durationMs: 82849 = ~83 sec) - SUCCESS with messageToolSentTo\n\n\n- 7719490 (durationMs: 150120 = ~2.5 min) - SUCCESS with messageToolSentTo\n- 7705086 (durationMs: 39698 = ~40 sec) - SUCCESS with messageToolSentTo\n\nThe pattern is clear: faster completions under 150 seconds succeeded with proper message delivery, while anything over 5 minutes hit idle timeouts. The model processes emails sequentially — reading headers, then content, then categorizing — which explains why it stalls on larger email volumes. I need to reduce the email batch size or optimize the reading flow so it can complete faster.\n","thinkingSignature":"4dc2e3b0872fbde644f6426b10e0ce0def28ce198c564a7763df62254f580157"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nThe test run just finished — status **OK** but it took **~5.15 min (309 sec)** and the summary delivered was just *\"I'll now execute the email processor skill step by step. First, let me check both inboxes simultaneously.\"* — meaning the model started reading the skill, began executing it, but didn't finish sending the actual email messages before the timeout hit again.\n\nLooking at the pattern across all successful runs:\n\n- ✅ **40-83 sec runs** → completed fast, sent proper messages\n- ✅ **~2.5 min runs** → completed fine\n- ❌ **5+ min runs** → hit or brushed against the idle timeout\n\nThe skill is more flexible than the old script but it also gives the model more things to do (full label classification, full body reading for ALL emails) which can slow it down. The old script was more \"railroaded\" which actually helped it finish faster.\n\nThe current setup with the skill is working but it's cutting it close. If timeouts keep happening, the fix would be to either:\n1. Simplify the skill to be more direct (fewer emails to check, faster classification)\n2. Go back to the old script which was faster due to being more constrained\n\nIt's running — just slower than ideal. Want me to look at optimizing the skill to be faster, or are you okay with it as-is for now?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":233,"output":568,"cacheRead":97440,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":98241,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777736620164,"responseId":"06454eac075b1befc7b5860ab8c79718"}}
