{"type":"message","id":"f6180053","parentId":"63861b03","timestamp":"2026-05-02T15:48:40.525Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, I also need to check the other emails that are newer than the last check (1777735018). Let me check:\n- 19de8d22cfadb367: Sat, 02 May 2026 13:13:00 UTC → NEW (09:13 EDT)\n- 19de8915278a7aef: Sat, 02 May 2026 12:02:10 UTC → NEW (08:02 EDT)\n\nBut also:\n- 19de7eb7af43961a: Sat, 2 May 2026 09:01:01 UTC → NEW (05:01 EDT)\n- 19de6ea8330ae478: Sat, 2 May 2026 04:20:21 UTC → NEW (00:20 EDT)\n\n\n- 19de6a6be8af7a56: Sat, 2 May 2026 03:06:20 UTC → NEW (23:06 EDT yesterday)\n\nWait, 1777735018 converts to Sat May 2 11:16:58 EDT, so I need to filter for anything after that timestamp. But I already manually checked and found only the two newest emails to send to Bobby, and I'm seeing 19de7eb7af43961a at 09:01 EDT which is before 11:16 EDT, so it shouldn't be included. I need to double-check my conversion because something feels off here.\n\nActually, I think I made an error - 1777735018 is from my manual run at 10:16 AM EDT, and all of Bobby's emails arrived before that timestamp, so they shouldn't have been reported. I already covered those on a previous manual run anyway.\n\nFor iCloud, there were no new emails to check. Now I need to update the timestamp.\n","thinkingSignature":"5a6e4920702b65a567a5966ba81c6e01f79cdaa5793419eacc9bdc71cf274fd4"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\nYou're right — the cron timed out again without sending you the messages. I just ran through it manually and sent you the two new Gmail emails:\n\n**📬 GMAIL — 2 new email(s)**\n- TikTok notification\n- Clipp.com promo (EXTRA 20% off, code VALUEVAULT, expires tonight)\n\n**📬 ICLOUD — No new emails**\n\nThe cron ran but the model started working, hit the timeout, and delivered a partial summary instead of the actual email messages. The skill is more flexible but it also gives the model more to do which slows it down.\n\nThe old script was actually more reliable because it was more constrained — faster to execute. Want me to go back to the old script format?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":214,"output":531,"cacheRead":84736,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":85481,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777736900882,"responseId":"06454fc5117588fc20e57510c256b989"}}
