{"type":"custom_message","customType":"openclaw.runtime-context","content":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"chat_id\": \"telegram:8212808444\",\n  \"message_id\": \"2348\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"8212808444\",\n  \"sender\": \"B G\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-05-02 12:00 EDT\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"B G (8212808444)\",\n  \"id\": \"8212808444\",\n  \"name\": \"B G\"\n}\n```","display":false,"details":{"source":"openclaw-runtime-context"},"id":"ea3b0e7a","parentId":"5680fcc1","timestamp":"2026-05-02T16:01:11.470Z"}
{"type":"message","id":"800c39db","parentId":"ea3b0e7a","timestamp":"2026-05-02T16:01:37.281Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby wants me to explain my current email checking process. Let me think through this carefully based on what we've set up.\n\nCurrent state:\n1. Cron job \"Emmy Email Check\" runs every hour\n2. It uses the email-processor skill at ~/.openclaw/skills/email-processor/SKILL.md\n3. The skill checks both Gmail and iCloud\n4. Sends separate Telegram messages for each\n\nBut we've been having issues with timeouts. Let me explain the process clearly and also note the issues we've been seeing.\n\nActually, let me think about what the ideal process should be vs what's actually happening:\n\n**Current setup:**\n- Cron job fires every hour\n- Model loads the skill and tries to execute it\n- Model searches Gmail + iCloud\n- Model reads new emails, categorizes them\n- Model sends Telegram messages\n\n**Problems:**\n- Model is slow because it has to load workspace context + skill\n- The skill has a lot of steps which slows execution\n- Timeout is ~5 minutes and we're often hitting it\n\nBobby wants to understand the process. Let me lay it out clearly, and maybe then we can fix what's broken.\n\nLet me read the current skill to give an accurate description.\n","thinkingSignature":"a2b468a7ac305e3c07afce2cf0b5975b0d7f8eb6adde14a3f9e52a168152f1f8"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nLet me walk you through exactly how it works today:\n\n**The Cron Job (\"Emmy Email Check\")**\n- Fires every hour (at the top of each hour)\n- Spawns an isolated session using MiniMax M2.7\n- Runs the email-processor skill\n\n**The Skill (`email-processor/SKILL.md`) does this:**\n\n**Gmail check:**\n1. Reads `last_email_check.timestamp` to know \"since when\"\n2. Searches Gmail for all unread inbox emails\n3. For each email → reads full content, checks if it's NEW (arrived after timestamp)\n4. Also checks Unroll.me/Unsubscribed for emails to restore\n5. Categorizes each NEW email: Urgent / Important / Low Priority\n6. Sends one Gmail Telegram message to you\n7. Updates the timestamp file\n\n**iCloud check:**\n1. Pulls credentials from macOS Keychain\n2. Searches INBOX for unseen messages\n3. Compares against `last_icloud_email_id.txt` checkpoint\n4. For new messages → fetches envelope (sender/subject)\n5. Categorizes with same urgency levels\n6. Sends one iCloud Telegram message to you\n7. Updates the iCloud checkpoint\n\n**The problem we've been hitting:**\nThe model loads your full workspace context (~50K tokens of SOUL.md, USER.md, MEMORY.md, etc.) before it even starts reading emails. Then it processes everything, and when MiniMax is slow that day, it hits the idle timeout before finishing and sending messages.\n\n**The fix I'd recommend:**\nSimplify the skill to be more direct — less context loading, fewer steps. Or switch back to the old script which was faster because it was more constrained.\n\nWhich do you want:\n1. **Simplify the skill** — keep the urgency categories, make it faster\n2. **Go back to the old script** — proven to work, less fancy formatting for iCloud\n3. **Keep it as-is** — works sometimes when MiniMax is fast"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":84891,"output":668,"cacheRead":192,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":85751,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777737671470,"responseId":"064552c884f1e9885d4d82c25d6e65e3"}}
