{"type":"message","id":"a8eb2101","parentId":"39b80ef0","timestamp":"2026-05-02T16:03:31.464Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby wants to know how I'd simplify the skill. Let me think about what makes the current skill slow and how to make it faster.\n\nThe current skill:\n1. Has a lot of context (label rules, interpretation rules, processing steps, message formats)\n2. The model reads the full SKILL.md file every time, which is loaded into context\n3. It has 12 labels to choose from and complex priority rules\n4. It requires reading full email bodies for every email\n5. iCloud requires more steps (checkpoint tracking, envelope fetching)\n\nSimplifications I could make:\n\n1. **Fewer labels** — collapse to just 3: Urgent, Important, Low Priority (matching what we actually message)\n2. **Shorter skill file** — cut out the verbose rules and just give direct steps\n3. **Skip full body reads** — only read body if sender/subject alone can't categorize\n4. **Use exec commands directly** — have the model run shell commands in a more railroaded way rather than making it \"figure out\" steps\n5. **Pre-filter at API level** — search for only emails since the last timestamp, not all emails then filter\n6. **Light context** — add `lightContext: true` to the cron job so it doesn't load the full workspace\n\nActually, I think the biggest win would be:\n1. Adding `lightContext: true` to the cron payload so it doesn't load the full workspace\n2. Shortening the skill to be more direct and prescriptive, less \"rules\" and more \"do this step\"\n3. Reducing the label categories to just the 3 we actually use\n\nLet me propose specific simplifications.\n","thinkingSignature":"16d418a060b930f3b5744a639bde11f74f29b39d6f2cb2ff8b24805c3b1bf264"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nHere's how I'd simplify it:\n\n**1. Shorten the skill file** — cut the verbose rules, make it direct steps only:\n- Current: ~200 lines with label rules, interpretation logic, priority order, etc.\n- Simplified: ~50 lines, just \"do this, then this, then send message\"\n\n**2. Fewer categories** — collapse from 12 labels to just 3:\n- 🔴 Urgent (bills, security, money)\n- 🟡 Important (orders, updates, personal)\n- ⚪ Low Priority (everything else)\n\n**3. Skip full body reads for most emails** — read header (sender + subject) first, only fetch body if it's not clear from headers alone\n\n**4. Lighten the context** — add `lightContext: true` to the cron so it doesn't load SOUL.md/MEMORY.md etc. every time. Just load the skill and go.\n\n**5. Pre-filter at search level** — instead of getting all unread then filtering by timestamp, search for emails newer than the last check timestamp directly\n\nThe old script was faster because it was essentially a straightjacket — do this exact command, then that exact command. The skill is smarter but slower because the model has to think through rules and make decisions at every step.\n\nWant me to rewrite the skill with these simplifications?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":85324,"output":625,"cacheRead":192,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":86141,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777737784233,"responseId":"0645533808dafb45d2c8e37cd191f8b7"}}
