{"type":"message","id":"151c422e","parentId":"186580d1","timestamp":"2026-05-02T16:06:53.205Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby wants to keep the 12 categories and full email body reading. He's asking about my list:\n\n1. Shorten the skill file - he didn't object to this\n2. Fewer categories - he wants to keep the 12 categories\n3. Skip full body reads - he wants full body reads kept\n4. Lighten the context - he doesn't know what this means\n5. Pre-filter at search level - he doesn't know what this means\n\nLet me explain #4 and #5 in plain terms, and confirm he's okay with the other changes.\n\n#4 (lighten context) = when the cron job runs, it loads all the workspace files (SOUL.md, USER.md, MEMORY.md, TOOLS.md, etc.) into the model's context. That's a lot of text before it even gets to the email skill. \"lightContext\" means we tell the system to NOT load those files, just load the skill and go.\n\n#5 (pre-filter at search level) = instead of getting ALL unread emails from Gmail then filtering them by timestamp, we search Gmail for emails that are specifically newer than our last check timestamp. It's a more targeted search so we get less data to process.\n\nLet me explain these to Bobby in plain English.\n","thinkingSignature":"8f16f1e087bd4cbe2700d00e6767cee8baf56c10a581a168d19d7a8aef71010d"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nGot it! So the 12 categories from the skill are:\n\n- 🔴 Bills/Payments\n- 🟡 Orders\n- 🔵 Updates\n- ⚪ Low Priority\n- + these from the original email-assistant skill:\n- Finance & Bills\n- Security\n- Personal\n- Shopping & Orders\n- Subscriptions\n- AI Tools\n- Social Media\n- Newsletters\n- Music & Beats\n- Gaming\n- Home Services\n- Job Search\n\n**Let me explain #4 and #5 in plain terms:**\n\n**#4 (Lighten the context)** — When the cron runs, the model has to first read a bunch of files about you (SOUL.md, USER.md, MEMORY.md, etc. — thousands of lines) before it can even start checking emails. That takes time. \"Lighten\" means we'd tell it to skip loading those files and just go straight to the email task.\n\n**#5 (Pre-filter at search level)** — Currently the system fetches ALL your unread emails from Gmail, then the model figures out which ones are new. A smarter way would be to tell Gmail \"only show emails newer than [last timestamp]\" so we get less data to sift through. Faster, less waste.\n\nSo the plan would be:\n- ✅ Keep the 12 categories\n- ✅ Read full email body (you're right, you need that accuracy)\n- ✅ Simplify the skill to be shorter/direct\n- ✅ Lighten context (skip loading those files)\n- ✅ Pre-filter at search level\n\nSound good?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":85671,"output":573,"cacheRead":192,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":86436,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777737989188,"responseId":"06455405f1f4b78411d253f4a5ed0bc8"}}
