{"type":"message","id":"2c89027a","parentId":"ee8e8a6a","timestamp":"2026-05-02T16:09:10.774Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby wants to see the format for both Gmail and iCloud messages. Let me think about the format based on the current skill and what we've been doing:\n\nFor Gmail:\n```\n📬 GMAIL — X new email(s)\n\n🔴 URGENT:\n• [Sender] — [Subject] → [Label]\n  └ [Preview snippet]\n\n🟡 IMPORTANT:\n• [Sender] — [Subject] → [Label]\n  └ [Preview snippet]\n\n⚪ LOW PRIORITY:\n• [Sender] — [Subject] → [Label]\n  └ [Preview snippet]\n\n\n```\n\nFor iCloud, the structure would mirror this with the same priority levels, sender, subject, and preview format. So I need to lay out what both Gmail and iCloud messages would look like when there are new emails, then show what gets sent when there are no new emails. Let me write this clearly for Bobby.\n","thinkingSignature":"ef67c665bd10d162ba9aa663cafda66ae541638f454da6ab037ef7b9571ab7b2"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nHere's how the Telegram messages would look:\n\n**GMAIL — with new emails:**\n```\n📬 GMAIL — 3 new email(s)\n\n🔴 URGENT:\n• Apple — An app-specific password was generated for your Apple Account.\n  └ Security alert — someone generated an app-specific password on your Apple account\n\n🟡 IMPORTANT:\n• Affirm — Your April Affirm Card statement is here\n  └ April statement now available in the Affirm app\n\n⚪ LOW PRIORITY:\n• TikTok — New notification from @username\n  └ Someone you follow just posted a new video\n```\n\n**GMAIL — no new emails:**\n```\n📬 GMAIL — No new emails\n```\n\n**ICLOUD — with new emails:**\n```\n📬 ICLOUD — 1 new email(s)\n\n🔴 URGENT:\n• Taylor Alexander — Re: Apartment Inquiry (Around mid June)\n  └ Following up on our conversation about the lease\n\n⚪ LOW PRIORITY:\n• RC Leasing — Re: Looking for new apartment\n  └ New listing available in your area\n```\n\n**ICLOUD — no new emails:**\n```\n📬 ICLOUD — No new emails\n```\n\nThat's the format — separate messages for Gmail and iCloud, organized by urgency, with sender, subject, label (for Gmail), and a snippet from the email body. Same format we use now, just delivered faster."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":86023,"output":472,"cacheRead":192,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":86687,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777738125717,"responseId":"0645548e7bc5f0071c89594394a592f5"}}
