{"type":"message","id":"7cfd9cf6","parentId":"d0244369","timestamp":"2026-05-02T16:14:35.936Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Actually, let me just write the simplified skill directly. I know what needs to be in it.\n","thinkingSignature":"ed91b40cb8d50c89ae60283d723682d4516f62144e79c81471110c43a1149428"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kdt4xgf4como_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# Email Processor Skill\n\nCheck Gmail and iCloud for new unread emails, read full content, label properly, and send clean Telegram reports.\n\n---\n\n## CATEGORIES (use one per email)\n\n- 🔴 Bills/Payments — bills, due dates, bank alerts, money owed\n- 🟡 Orders — shipping, receipts, order updates, confirmations\n- 🔵 Updates — security alerts, account changes, service notices\n- ⚪ Low Priority — newsletters, promos, marketing, social\n\n---\n\n## GMAIL STEPS\n\n1. Get last check time: `cat ~/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_email_check.timestamp` (use 0 if missing)\n2. Search unread inbox: `gog gmail search \"is:unread in:inbox\" --max 30 --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com`\n3. For each email — read full body: `gog gmail get <msg_id> --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com`\n4. Check if `date > last_check` — skip if already reported\n5. Label by category above\n6. Mark read: `gog gmail batch modify <msg_id> --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com --remove UNREAD`\n7. Send Gmail report to 8212808444\n8. Update timestamp: `echo $(date +%s) > ~/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_email_check.timestamp`\n\n## GMAIL MESSAGE FORMAT\n```\n📬 GMAIL — X new email(s)\n\n🔴 URGENT:\n• [Sender] — [Subject] —> [Label]\n  └ [1-line snippet from email body]\n\n🟡 IMPORTANT:\n• [Sender] — [Subject] —> [Label]\n  └ [1-line snippet]\n\n⚪ LOW PRIORITY:\n• [Sender] — [Subject] —> [Label]\n  └ [1-line snippet]\n```\nIf no new: `📬 GMAIL — No new emails`\n\n---\n\n## ICLOUD STEPS\n\n1. Get credentials: `ICLOUD_CREDS=$(security find-generic-password -a \"rtg.bobby@icloud.com\" -s \"emmy-icloud-email\" -w 2>/dev/null)`\n2. Search unseen: `curl -s --url \"imaps://imap.mail.me.com/INBOX\" --user \"rtg.bobby@icloud.com:$ICLOUD_CREDS\" -X \"SEARCH UNSEEN\" 2>&1`\n3. Get checkpoint: `cat ~/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_icloud_email_id.txt` (use 0 if missing)\n4. Only process msg_num > checkpoint\n5. Fetch envelope: `curl -s --url \"imaps://imap.mail.me.com/INBOX\" --user \"rtg.bobby@icloud.com:$ICLOUD_CREDS\" -X \"FETCH <msg_num>:* (ENVELOPE)\" 2>&1`\n6. Label by urgency (no label needed for iCloud — just sender/subject/snippet)\n7. Update checkpoint: `echo <highest_msg_num> > ~/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_icloud_email_id.txt`\n8. Send iCloud report to 8212808444\n\n## ICLOUD MESSAGE FORMAT\n```\n📬 ICLOUD — X new email(s)\n\n🔴 URGENT:\n• [Sender] — [Subject]\n  └ [1-line snippet]\n\n🟡 IMPORTANT:\n• [Sender] — [Subject]\n  └ [1-line snippet]\n\n⚪ LOW PRIORITY:\n• [Sender] — [Subject]\n  └ [1-line snippet]\n```\nIf no new: `📬 ICLOUD — No new emails`\n\n---\n\n## RULES\n- Read FULL email body for classification — not just headers\n- Always send both Gmail AND iCloud reports (even if empty)\n- Always update timestamps AFTER sending reports\n- Categorize by email CONTENT and INTENT, not just sender name\n- If unsure about a category, pick the closest match and move on","path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/skills/email-processor/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":109,"output":900,"cacheRead":86592,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":87601,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777738448909,"responseId":"064555d1bb183fb6614b232bf6d2c2b3"}}
