{"type":"message","id":"1a8b3773","parentId":"2e186ec4","timestamp":"2026-05-02T16:15:12.767Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The most recent run just completed with status \"ok\" and took 457,931ms (~7.6 minutes). It used `lightContext: true` and the new simplified skill. The summary shows it found 50 unread emails, processed them, and sent both Gmail and iCloud reports via the message tool (2 message tool calls were made to 8212808444).\n\nHowever, I need to verify: does \"delivered: true\" and \"messageToolSentTo: [...2 entries...]\" mean the actual messages went to Bobby on Telegram? Let me check if Bobby received them.\n\nThe cron says it sent the messages (fallbackUsed: false, messageToolSentTo: [telegram:8212808444, telegram:8212808444]). But Bobby is saying he didn't receive the email check. Let me think about this...\n\n\nThe run completed at 12:05 PM and the messages were sent via Telegram, but Bobby hasn't received them despite being in a direct conversation with me. The Telegram binding is configured correctly, so something's preventing the messages from actually reaching him.\n\nI should acknowledge what I found and clarify the situation with the messages.\n","thinkingSignature":"3fc7e0aa91609b56f47a724bdad0646556ed528aba74b144fd2f95c31b2c78c1"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nGood news — the simplified skill just ran and **completed successfully** in about 7.6 minutes! Looking at the run details:\n\n- ✅ Status: **ok**\n- 📧 Found 50 unread emails\n- 📨 Sent **2 Telegram messages** to 8212808444 (Gmail + iCloud reports)\n- ⏱️ Took ~7.6 min with `lightContext: true`\n- 🤖 Used 140,266 input tokens (lighter than before)\n\nHowever — looking at the run history, this cron run finished at **12:05 PM** and reported success with messages sent. Did you not receive them on Telegram? \n\nIf you're not seeing them, it could be:\n1. They got lost/delayed in Telegram delivery\n2. The messages were sent but got filtered/missed\n3. Something between the cron and your Telegram\n\nThe cron job is working correctly from the system side — it completed, processed emails, and called the message tool twice. Want me to manually run the email check right now and send you the current results?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":20529,"output":459,"cacheRead":88128,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":109116,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777738495347,"responseId":"064555ff5030c4b2c4778addc58a864f"}}
