{"type":"message","id":"cbce8c44","parentId":"9db2f447","timestamp":"2026-05-02T16:23:45.948Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wow, there are A LOT of unread emails. Let me focus on the ones that are truly NEW and urgent. Let me think about what we already covered:\n\nEarlier today I already sent Bobby:\n1. Apple security alert (app-specific password generated) - May 1, 23:06\n2. Affirm April statement - May 2, 05:01\n3. X Developer Platform $10 receipt - May 1, 22:38\n4. Y-12 eStatement - May 1, 19:12\n5. TikTok notification - May 2, 09:13\n6. Clipp.com promo - May 2, 08:02\n\n\n7. Apple Music for Artists weekly recap - May 2, 00:20\n\nNow I need to check what's actually new since the last check at 11:58 AM. Looking at the emails that came in after that cutoff time, there's really just the two TikTok and Clipp notifications. But wait—I'm realizing the actual issue here: we started with 50 unread emails, and this list is showing all of them. The timestamp filtering should be catching the new ones, but something's off with how that's working.\n\nActually, what I should be focused on is what Bobby would consider genuinely new and actionable. The security alerts, bills, and payment notices are what matter—those are the ones that actually need attention or action from him. Let me pull out just those critical ones from the full unread list and get those sent over as a clean summary.\n","thinkingSignature":"45699dda841262229e04ce3506a8a4d22a642252f0e4354375da78b72139cfa1"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nFair! Let me go through everything fresh now. Give me a minute — there's a LOT of unread emails.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_oadi354w0fwz_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"gog gmail get 19de01ccc7324c0b --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com 2>&1 | grep -E \"^(from|subject|date)\" | head -3","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":3331,"output":413,"cache