{"type":"message","id":"9d87541e","parentId":"6ebc3137","timestamp":"2026-05-02T16:23:56.430Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to focus on NEW emails since the last successful cron run. Let me check what emails arrived after 11:58 AM today (May 2) by reading the full body of the 2 most recent ones and checking their timestamps.\n\nThe timestamps from the search results:\n- TikTok: May 2 09:13 UTC (5:13 AM EDT)  \n- Clipp.com: May 2 08:02 UTC (4:02 AM EDT)\n- etc.\n\nWait, these are from overnight. The last successful cron was at 11:58 AM and the one that ran at 12:05 PM found 50 unread emails. Let me check if any emails arrived AFTER 11:58 AM EDT (which is 15:58 UTC).\n\n\nNow I'm converting 11:58 AM EDT to UTC—that's 15:58—and scanning through the timestamps to see which emails came in after that cutoff time. I'm seeing a couple from this morning that fit the criteria, so let me verify those by checking the full message details and then I'll need to pull the iCloud email to complete this check.\n","thinkingSignature":"3e7b83f4cf8765793cc3cf16e550b7a0520523ece167b0ac3b85d8cc1d2b3370"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cy0la4tzx115_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"gog gmail get 19de8d22cfadb367 --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com 2>&1 | tail -5 && echo \"===\" && gog gmail get 19de8915278a7aef --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com 2>&1 | tail -5","timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":197,"output":327,"cacheRead":101120,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":101644,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777739026339,"responseId":"064558124a6d2083a695c289ce14ccd4"}}
