{"type":"message","id":"c0455ef8","parentId":"c2b08eb8","timestamp":"2026-05-02T16:26:53.638Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user noticed I sent them both Gmail and iCloud in one message. They want 2 separate Telegram messages - one for Gmail and one for iCloud. Let me check the skill to confirm it says to send separate messages.\n\nLooking at the skill I wrote:\n```\n## GMAIL MESSAGE FORMAT\n...\n## ICLOUD MESSAGE FORMAT\n```\n\nAnd the cron job instruction says: \"Send Gmail results and iCloud results as separate Telegram messages to 8212808444.\"\n\nSo the skill does say to send separate messages. But in my one-shot, I combined them into one message. That's fine for the one-shot but the skill correctly says to send two separate messages.\n\n\nNow I need to double-check the skill to make sure it's clear about sending these as two separate messages back-to-back.\n","thinkingSignature":"78dc11b94b6f509d541b58cdaf081752658e70f697cda5c1db5bf3054000426e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5epzlko7zrzj_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/skills/email-processor/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":104513,"output":202,"cacheRead":128,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":104843,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777739199512,"responseId":"064558c0685b1c854b0404864d2c6c93"}}
{"type":"message","id":"b0b1ed35","parentId":"c0455ef8","timestamp":"2026-05-02T16:27:00.348Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_5epzlko7zrzj_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Email Processor Skill\n\nCheck Gmail and iCloud for new unread emails, read full content, label properly, and send clean Telegram reports.\n\n---\n\n## CATEGORIES (use one per email)\n\n- 🔴 Bills/Payments — bills, due dates, bank alerts, money owed\n- 🟡 Orders — shipping, receipts, order updates, confirmations\n- 🔵 Updates — security alerts, account changes, service notices\n- ⚪ Low Priority — newsletters, promos, marketing, social\n\n---\n\n## GMAIL STEPS\n\n1. Get last check time: `cat ~/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_email_check.timestamp` (use 0 if missing)\n2. Search unread inbox: `gog gmail search \"is:unread in:inbox\" --max 30 --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com`\n3. For each email — read full body: `gog gmail get <msg_id> --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com`\n4. Check if `date > last_check` — skip if already reported\n5. Label by category above\n6. Mark read: `gog gmail batch modify <msg_id> --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com --remove UNREAD`\n7. Send Gmail report to 8212808444\n8. Update timestamp: `echo $(date +%s) > ~/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_email_check.timestamp`\n\n## GMAIL MESSAGE FORMAT\n```\n📬 GMAIL — X new email(s)\n\n🔴 URGENT:\n• [Sender] — [Subject] —> [Label]\n  └ [1-line snippet from email body]\n\n🟡 IMPORTANT:\n• [Sender] — [Subject] —> [Label]\n  └ [1-line snippet]\n\n⚪ LOW PRIORITY:\n• [Sender] — [Subject] —> [Label]\n  └ [1-line snippet]\n```\nIf no new: `📬 GMAIL — No new emails`\n\n---\n\n## ICLOUD STEPS\n\n1. Get credentials: `ICLOUD_CREDS=$(security find-generic-password -a \"rtg.bobby@icloud.com\" -s \"emmy-icloud-email\" -w 2>/dev/null)`\n2. Search unseen: `curl -s --url \"imaps://imap.mail.me.com/INBOX\" --user \"rtg.bobby@icloud.com:$ICLOUD_CREDS\" -X \"SEARCH UNSEEN\" 2>&1`\n3. Get checkpoint: `cat ~/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_icloud_email_id.txt` (use 0 if missing)\n4. Only process msg_num > checkpoint\n5. Fetch envelope: `curl -s --url \"imaps://imap.mail.me.com/INBOX\" --user \"rtg.bobby@icloud.com:$ICLOUD_CREDS\" -X \"FETCH <msg_num>:* (ENVELOPE)\" 2>&1`\n6. Label by urgency (no label needed for iCloud — just sender/subject/snippet)\n7. Update checkpoint: `echo <highest_msg_num> > ~/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_icloud_email_id.txt`\n8. Send iCloud report to 8212808444\n\n## ICLOUD MESSAGE FORMAT\n```\n📬 ICLOUD — X new email(s)\n\n🔴 URGENT:\n• [Sender] — [Subject]\n  └ [1-line snippet]\n\n🟡 IMPORTANT:\n• [Sender] — [Subject]\n  └ [1-line snippet]\n\n⚪ LOW PRIORITY:\n• [Sender] — [Subject]\n  └ [1-line snippet]\n```\nIf no new: `📬 ICLOUD — No new emails`\n\n---\n\n## RULES\n- Read FULL email body for classification — not just headers\n- Always send both Gmail AND iCloud reports (even if empty)\n- Always update timestamps AFTER sending reports\n- Categorize by email CONTENT and INTENT, not just sender name\n- If unsure about a category, pick the closest match and move on"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1777739220348}}
{"type":"message","id":"4d0ae3ca","parentId":"b0b1ed35","timestamp":"2026-05-02T16:27:18.642Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The skill already has both Gmail and iCloud steps with separate message formats, and it says to send both reports. But the user is right - in the one-shot I just did, I put them together in one message because it was just for me to show him. The skill already has them as separate messages. But let me re-read the skill to make sure the \"send separately back to back\" is clear.\n\nThe skill says:\n- Step 7: \"Send Gmail report to 8212808444\"\n- Step 8: \"Send iCloud report to 8212808444\"\n\nAnd under Gmail message format it shows the Gmail format, and under iCloud it shows the iCloud format. \n\nLooking at the ICLOUD STEPS section, I see it mentions labeling by urgency but the message format doesn't actually include the label field - it just shows sender and subject. The skill structure itself is clear that there are two separate steps for sending each report, so the messaging is already set up to go out individually rather than combined.\n\nBut I'm realizing the real issue: when I did the one-shot, I sent one combined message instead of following the skill's two-step flow. The skill already has the right structure with separate steps, but maybe I need to emphasize in the rules that Gmail report comes first, then iCloud report immediately after, and they're always distinct messages rather than one consolidated one.\n","thinkingSignature":"4c716c2d649cb37567f94d989e1bfdf680e12252fe202a0c45cc76b3805c20de"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nYes, the skill already sends them separately — the Gmail message first, then the iCloud message right after. They're on separate steps (Gmail step 7, iCloud step 8). I just combined them in my one-shot reply because it was easier to show you everything at once.\n\nThe skill already has it correct:\n- **Gmail message** → sent to 8212808444 (step 7)\n- **iCloud message** → sent immediately after to 8212808444 (step 8)\n\nEach one is a separate Telegram message. The cron will deliver them back-to-back on Telegram.\n\nIs there anything else you want adjusted before we let the cron take over?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1012,"output":426,"cacheRead":104512,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":105950,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777739220352,"responseId":"064558d9e635942e9231af92adb76e76"}}
