{"type":"message","id":"2aa7ec0d","parentId":"b6a6200c","timestamp":"2026-05-02T17:10:11.545Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_uc8mx0ctr0ka_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"ID                DATE              FROM                                    SUBJECT                                                                        LABELS                                      THREAD\n19de8d22cfadb367  2026-05-02 09:13  TikTok <newsletter@service.tiktok.com>  🗡️: do you guys know what i’m talking about please tell me you do im not s...  CATEGORY_PROMOTIONS,UNREAD,IMPORTANT,INBOX  -\n19de8915278a7aef  2026-05-02 08:02  \"Clipp.com\" <noreply@clipp.com>         The Vault's Open: EXTRA Savings Inside!                                        CATEGORY_PROMOTIONS,UNREAD,INBOX            -"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1120,"aggregated":"ID                DATE              FROM                                    SUBJECT                                                                        LABELS                                      THREAD\n19de8d22cfadb367  2026-05-02 09:13  TikTok <newsletter@service.tiktok.com>  🗡️: do you guys know what i’m talking about please tell me you do im not s...  CATEGORY_PROMOTIONS,UNREAD,IMPORTANT,INBOX  -\n19de8915278a7aef  2026-05-02 08:02  \"Clipp.com\" <noreply@clipp.com>         The Vault's Open: EXTRA Savings Inside!                                        CATEGORY_PROMOTIONS,UNREAD,INBOX            -","cwd":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777741811545}}
{"type":"message","id":"bec36e6a","parentId":"2aa7ec0d","timestamp":"2026-05-02T17:10:37.099Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Using Gmail's `after:` search filter shows only 2 unread emails from today (both before 1 PM). The most recent email was at 9:13 AM. So there truly are no emails that arrived AFTER 1 PM today.\n\nLet me check the dates more carefully:\n- TikTok: 09:13 AM today\n- Clipp.com: 08:02 AM today\n\nThese are the only 2 emails today. Both came before 1 PM. So the cron at 12:58 PM reporting emails from today was indeed giving old emails.\n\nThe issue was that the skill was reporting ALL unread emails, not filtering by the timestamp. The timestamp check isn't working correctly in the skill. Let me verify the dates.\n\n\nI see the problem now—the cron ran successfully and sent those messages, but it's reporting emails from this morning at 9:13 AM without properly checking when they were actually received. Looking at the search results and the cron summary, it's clear the timestamp filtering logic isn't being applied correctly.\n\nThe model is correctly fetching emails within the last hour (since 12:03 PM), but it's not validating whether they arrived after the last_check timestamp—it just displays them with a vague description like \"Found 50 unread emails\" without verifying their actual receive times against the timestamp comparison.\n\nThe fix is to ensure the skill's step 4 properly skips emails where `date <= last_check`, so we don't report emails that were already processed in previous runs. right email timestamps. The gog `date` field gives timestamps in RFC 2822 format, but the last_check timestamp is Unix epoch time, so the comparison logic is tricky. When I manually ran it, I filtered by checking if the email's Unix timestamp (internalDate from the header) was greater than the last_check epoch, but the skill doesn't explicitly extract internalDate—it only displays the human-readable date, which is where the logic breaks down.\n\nThe real issue is that the skill model tries to parse the date field and do the comparison, but it keeps reporting emails that are actually older than the last_check timestamp, suggesting the timestamp check isn't working correctly. I set last_email_check.timestamp to the cron run time at 11:58 AM, so any email from 9:13 AM should be filtered out, yet the cron still reported them.\n\nLooking at the cron summary, it claims to have searched for emails newer than 11:58 AM and found 50 unread, but the TikTok email that came in at 9:13 AM shouldn't have been included in those results if the timestamp filtering was actually working. The model is likely skipping the timestamp check entirely and just reporting all unread emails.\n\nI need to update the skill to be more explicit about extracting and comparing the internalDate timestamp from each email, rather than relying on the human-readable date field which could be ambiguous or in a different timezone.","thinkingSignature":"23bda2b7fd7d9bc80aa8e26bf7ac3924dfeffecdd99c1dfe317f710709294702"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nYou're right — no new emails have come in since 9:13 AM this morning. The cron at 12:58 PM was showing you emails from the entire unread inbox, not filtering by the timestamp.\n\nThe problem is in the skill — the timestamp check isn't working correctly. The model is reporting all unread emails instead of comparing the email timestamps to the last check time.\n\nLet me fix the skill to be clearer about the timestamp check:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_havp0fxknsbh_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"edits":[{"newText":"3. For each email found — run: gog gmail get <msg_id> --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com\n4. In the output, find the INTERNALDATE timestamp (Unix epoch — a large number like 1777735018). This is when Gmail actually received the email.\n5. ONLY process if internalDate > LAST_CHECK_EPOCH. Skip emails with internalDate <= LAST_CHECK_EPOCH.\n6. For each NEW email (internalDate > LAST_CHECK): read full body, label by category","oldText":"3. For each email — read full body: gog gmail get <msg_id> --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com\n4. Check if `date > last_check` — skip if already reported\n5. Label by category above"}],"path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/skills/email-processor/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":250,"output":893,"cacheRead":106336,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":107479,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777741811547,"responseId":"064562f63c8bca755f204be6909f7b2c"}}
{"type":"message","id":"4a1193d9","parentId":"bec36e6a","timestamp":"2026-05-02T17:10:37.110Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_havp0fxknsbh_1","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"status\": \"error\",\n  \"tool\": \"edit\",\n  \"error\": \"Could not find the exact text in /Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/skills/email-processor/SKILL.md. The old text must match exactly including all whitespace and newlines.\\nCurrent file contents:\\n# Email Processor Skill\\n\\nCheck Gmail and iCloud for new unread emails, read full content, label properly, and send clean Telegram reports.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## CATEGORIES (use one per email)\\n\\n- 🔴 Bills/Payments — bills, due dates, bank alerts, money owed\\n- 🟡 Orders — shipping, receipts, order updates, confirmations\\n- 🔵 Updates — security alerts, account changes, service notices\\n- ⚪ Low Priority — newsletters, promos, marketing, social\\n\\n---\\n\\n## GMAIL STEPS\\n\\n1. Get last check time: `cat ~/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_email_check.timestamp` (use 0 if missing)\\n2. Search unread inbox: `gog gmail search \\\"is:unread in:inbox\\\" --max 30 --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com`\\n3. For each email — read full body: `gog gmail get <msg_id> --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com`\\n4. Check if `date > last_check` — skip if already r\\n... (truncated)\"\n}"}],"details":{"status":"error","tool":"edit","error":"Could not find the exact text in /Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/skills/email-processor/SKILL.md. The old text must match exactly including all whitespace and newlines.\nCurrent file contents:\n# Email Processor Skill\n\nCheck Gmail and iCloud for new unread emails, read full content, label properly, and send clean Telegram reports.\n\n---\n\n## CATEGORIES (use one per email)\n\n- 🔴 Bills/Payments — bills, due dates, bank alerts, money owed\n- 🟡 Orders — shipping, receipts, order updates, confirmations\n- 🔵 Updates — security alerts, account changes, service notices\n- ⚪ Low Priority — newsletters, promos, marketing, social\n\n---\n\n## GMAIL STEPS\n\n1. Get last check time: `cat ~/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_email_check.timestamp` (use 0 if missing)\n2. Search unread inbox: `gog gmail search \"is:unread in:inbox\" --max 30 --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com`\n3. For each email — read full body: `gog gmail get <msg_id> --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com`\n4. Check if `date > last_check` — skip if already r\n... (truncated)"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777741837110}}
{"type":"message","id":"a5e56aa8","parentId":"4a1193d9","timestamp":"2026-05-02T17:10:38.443Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me read the full file first to get the exact content.","thinkingSignature":"e0d655b87dd9680f4f7c0924706751422a62109dedb2f90ce3b8d3440e862205"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ysn8eqp56v6g_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/skills/email-processor/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":566,"output":56,"cacheRead":106560,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":107182,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777741837113,"responseId":"0645630d1661af87027ef92f70fde3b3"}}
{"type":"message","id":"70e2ea96","parentId":"a5e56aa8","timestamp":"2026-05-02T17:10:38.458Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ysn8eqp56v6g_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Email Processor Skill\n\nCheck Gmail and iCloud for new unread emails, read full content, label properly, and send clean Telegram reports.\n\n---\n\n## CATEGORIES (use one per email)\n\n- 🔴 Bills/Payments — bills, due dates, bank alerts, money owed\n- 🟡 Orders — shipping, receipts, order updates, confirmations\n- 🔵 Updates — security alerts, account changes, service notices\n- ⚪ Low Priority — newsletters, promos, marketing, social\n\n---\n\n## GMAIL STEPS\n\n1. Get last check time: `cat ~/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_email_check.timestamp` (use 0 if missing)\n2. Search unread inbox: `gog gmail search \"is:unread in:inbox\" --max 30 --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com`\n3. For each email — read full body: `gog gmail get <msg_id> --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com`\n4. Check if `date > last_check` — skip if already reported\n5. Label by category above\n6. Mark read: `gog gmail batch modify <msg_id> --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com --remove UNREAD`\n7. Send Gmail report to 8212808444\n8. Update timestamp: `echo $(date +%s) > ~/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_email_check.timestamp`\n\n## GMAIL MESSAGE FORMAT\n```\n📬 GMAIL — X new email(s)\n\n🔴 URGENT:\n• [Sender] — [Subject] —> [Label]\n  └ [1-line snippet from email body]\n\n🟡 IMPORTANT:\n• [Sender] — [Subject] —> [Label]\n  └ [1-line snippet]\n\n⚪ LOW PRIORITY:\n• [Sender] — [Subject] —> [Label]\n  └ [1-line snippet]\n```\nIf no new: `📬 GMAIL — No new emails`\n\n---\n\n## ICLOUD STEPS\n\n1. Get credentials: `ICLOUD_CREDS=$(security find-generic-password -a \"rtg.bobby@icloud.com\" -s \"emmy-icloud-email\" -w 2>/dev/null)`\n2. Search unseen: `curl -s --url \"imaps://imap.mail.me.com/INBOX\" --user \"rtg.bobby@icloud.com:$ICLOUD_CREDS\" -X \"SEARCH UNSEEN\" 2>&1`\n3. Get checkpoint: `cat ~/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_icloud_email_id.txt` (use 0 if missing)\n4. Only process msg_num > checkpoint\n5. Fetch envelope: `curl -s --url \"imaps://imap.mail.me.com/INBOX\" --user \"rtg.bobby@icloud.com:$ICLOUD_CREDS\" -X \"FETCH <msg_num>:* (ENVELOPE)\" 2>&1`\n6. Label by urgency (no label needed for iCloud — just sender/subject/snippet)\n7. Update checkpoint: `echo <highest_msg_num> > ~/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_icloud_email_id.txt`\n8. Send iCloud report to 8212808444\n\n## ICLOUD MESSAGE FORMAT\n```\n📬 ICLOUD — X new email(s)\n\n🔴 URGENT:\n• [Sender] — [Subject]\n  └ [1-line snippet]\n\n🟡 IMPORTANT:\n• [Sender] — [Subject]\n  └ [1-line snippet]\n\n⚪ LOW PRIORITY:\n• [Sender] — [Subject]\n  └ [1-line snippet]\n```\nIf no new: `📬 ICLOUD — No new emails`\n\n---\n\n## RULES\n- Read FULL email body for classification — not just headers\n- Always send both Gmail AND iCloud reports (even if empty)\n- Always update timestamps AFTER sending reports\n- Categorize by email CONTENT and INTENT, not just sender name\n- If unsure about a category, pick the closest match and move on"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1777741838458}}
{"type":"message","id":"403d7790","parentId":"70e2ea96","timestamp":"2026-05-02T17:10:43.976Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is that `gog gmail get` doesn't return the internalDate/epoch timestamp. Looking at the email search output, the \"DATE\" column shows the date string but doesn't give the Unix epoch. The actual filtering in the skill step 4 says \"Check if `date > last_check`\" but \"date\" is not the epoch timestamp - it's just a human readable date string.\n\nThe `gog gmail search` command doesn't return the internalDate either. The search output just shows a human-readable date.\n\nSo the model is comparing dates like \"Sat, 02 May 2026 13:13:00 +0000 (UTC)\" with a Unix epoch timestamp like \"1777741422\" - which won't work correctly.\n \nThe search results do show IDs though, and I could potentially fetch all emails newer than the last check time using a date filter. But `gog gmail search` doesn't actually support searching by Unix timestamp internally - it only supports the `after:` and `before:` operators with date formats like `YYYY/MM/DD`. The real problem is that the ID structure might encode timestamp information, so I should check what those IDs actually represent.\n","thinkingSignature":"85f6660a3d839ed4d3af18ac6619e07e977edb9b806fe1e4f5714e937a8b6522"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9ebrd40oqm83_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"gog gmail get 19de8d22cfadb367 --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com 2>&1 | head -10","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":904,"output":302,"cacheRead":107104,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":108310,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777741838464,"responseId":"0645630ecda835304cdbee316279e4dd"}}
