{"type":"message","id":"2989584c","parentId":"256ea716","timestamp":"2026-05-02T18:07:23.673Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The last email check timestamp is 1777744788, which is 13:59:48 EDT. Let me check if there's a previous timestamp to calculate the window, or if I should also check what the current timestamp is.\n\nActually, the timestamp 1777744788 = Sat May 2 13:59:48 EDT 2026. That means the last successful run was at 13:59:48. The current time would be around when the user is asking this. Let me check what the current time is.\n\nSo the current timestamp is 1777744788 = 13:59:48 EDT. This means the last email check ran at 13:59:48 and the timestamp was updated to that. The previous timestamp would have been... let me think about when the cron ran. It fires every 3600000ms = 1 hour. The schedule anchor was at 1773961081922ms. The last run at 1777744788000ms = 1777744788 seconds.\n\n\nSo the cron job runs hourly at about 58 minutes past each hour. If the last run was at 13:59:48, then the next one should be around 14:58. Looking back at the previous runs, the one that reported 49 unread emails ran from 11:58 to 12:05, which means that timestamp was from the last successful run.\n\nNow I need to trace when the timestamp actually got updated to 1777744788 by going through the cron run history.\n","thinkingSignature":"d4c2d71649ef7804bd5ad67a84f45c0fb11731cd971c83dcc7e557b542752913"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_h64sjoju3tle_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"date && echo \"---\" && cat /Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_email_check.timestamp && echo \"---\" && date -r $(cat /Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_email_check.timestamp)"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":112,"output":393,"cacheRead":110112,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":110617,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"st