{"type":"message","id":"041c5d83","parentId":"da747301","timestamp":"2026-05-02T18:18:35.627Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"We need to go BACKWARDS in time to set the timestamp to 14:00 (the start of the current hour), not forward. Let me think about this differently.The problem is that the timestamp represents \"I've already checked up to this point.\" When the cron runs, it checks emails NEWER than the timestamp.\n\nSo if the timestamp is set to 14:00, and the cron runs at 15:00, it'll show all emails from 14:00 to 15:00.\n\nBut if the timestamp is set to 14:17 (now), and cron runs at 15:00, it would show emails from 14:17 to 15:00 — missing 14:00-14:17.\n\nThe issue is: we want the cron to check a FIXED one-hour window based on the clock, not based on when it last ran.\n\nOption 1: The skill should calculate \"one hour ago\" each time it runs.\nOption 2: We use a different timestamp approach — maybe the cron should set the timestamp to the start of the current hour AFTER sending the report (but then it would miss emails from 14:00-14:17).\n\nThe REAL issue is that the timestamp is a moving target. The fix should be in the skill logic: instead of comparing against a stored timestamp, the skill should ALWAYS check emails from exactly 1 hour ago to now.\n\nLet me update the skill to use a relative time instead of an absolute timestamp.\n","thinkingSignature":"95bc759ddab27b27856550fd5deb73100c7f94d2e2a94dc5127d67e0cc98e341"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8dgfnboijsf6_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# Email Processor Skill\n\nCheck Gmail and iCloud for new unread emails, read full content, label properly, and send clean Telegram reports.\n\n---\n\n## CATEGORIES (use one per email)\n\n- 🔴 Bills/Payments — bills, due dates, bank alerts, money owed\n- 🟡 Orders — shipping, receipts, order updates, confirmations\n- 🔵 Updates — security alerts, account changes, service notices\n- ⚪ Low Priority — newsletters, promos, marketing, social\n\n---\n\n## GMAIL STEPS\n\n1. Calculate one hour ago as Unix epoch: `python3 -c \"import time; print(int(time.time() - 3600))\"`\n   This is your LAST_CHECK — the start of the 1-hour window.\n2. Search unread inbox: `gog gmail search \"is:unread in:inbox\" --max 30 --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com`\n3. For each email, get the date string from gog output (format: \"Sat, 02 May 2026 13:13:00 +0000 (UTC)\")\n4. Convert date string to Unix epoch using:\n   ```\n   python3 -c \"import email.utils,sys; dt=email.utils.parsedate_to_datetime(sys.stdin.read().strip()); print(int(dt.timestamp()))\"\n   ```\n5. Only process if Unix epoch > LAST_CHECK. Skip if epoch <= LAST_CHECK.\n6. For each NEW email — read full body: `gog gmail get <msg_id> --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com`\n7. Label by category above\n8. Mark read: `gog gmail batch modify <msg_id> --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com --remove UNREAD`\n9. Send Gmail report to 8212808444 (MUST be a separate message from iCloud report)\n10. Update timestamp: `echo $(date +%s) > ~/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_email_check.timestamp`\n\n## GMAIL MESSAGE FORMAT (send as ONE message to 8212808444)\n```\n📬 GMAIL — X new email(s)\n\n🔴 URGENT:\n• [Sender] — [Subject] —> [Label]\n  └ [1-line snippet from email body]\n\n🟡 IMPORTANT:\n• [Sender] — [Subject] —> [Label]\n  └ [1-line snippet]\n\n⚪ LOW PRIORITY:\n• [Sender] — [Subject] —> [Label]\n  └ [1-line snippet]\n```\nIf no new: `📬 GMAIL — No new emails`\n\n---\n\n## ICLOUD STEPS\n\n1. Get credentials: `ICLOUD_CREDS=$(security find-generic-password -a \"rtg.bobby@icloud.com\" -s \"emmy-icloud-email\" -w 2>/dev/null)`\n2. Search unseen: `curl -s --url \"imaps://imap.mail.me.com/INBOX\" --user \"rtg.bobby@icloud.com:$ICLOUD_CREDS\" -X \"SEARCH UNSEEN\" 2>&1`\n3. Get checkpoint: `cat ~/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_icloud_email_id.txt` (use 0 if missing)\n4. Only process msg_num > checkpoint\n5. Fetch envelope: `curl -s --url \"imaps://imap.mail.me.com/INBOX\" --user \"rtg.bobby@icloud.com:$ICLOUD_CREDS\" -X \"FETCH <msg_num>:* (ENVELOPE)\" 2>&1`\n6. For each new message, label by urgency (no category label needed — just sender/subject/snippet)\n7. Update checkpoint: `echo <highest_msg_num> > ~/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_icloud_email_id.txt`\n8. Send iCloud report to 8212808444 (MUST be a separate message from Gmail report)\n\n## ICLOUD MESSAGE FORMAT (send as ONE message to 8212808444, AFTER Gmail message)\n```\n📬 ICLOUD — X new email(s)\n\n🔴 URGENT:\n• [Sender] — [Subject]\n  └ [1-line snippet]\n\n🟡 IMPORTANT:\n• [Sender] — [Subject]\n  └ [1-line snippet]\n\n⚪ LOW PRIORITY:\n• [Sender] — [Subject]\n  └ [1-line snippet]\n```\nIf no new: `📬 ICLOUD — No new emails`\n\n---\n\n## CRITICAL RULES\n- Gmail AND iCloud reports MUST be sent as TWO SEPARATE Telegram messages\n- Send Gmail report FIRST, then iCloud report immediately after\n- The 1-hour window is calculated dynamically using `time.time() - 3600` at runtime — NOT from the timestamp file\n- The timestamp file is updated AFTER sending reports, for iCloud checkpoint purposes only\n- Read FULL email body for classification — not just headers\n- Categorize by email CONTENT and INTENT, not just sender name\n- If unsure about a category, pick the closest match and move on","path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/skills/email-processor/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":132,"output":1393,"cacheRead":110528,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":112053,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777745883218,"responseId":"064572db514a80f538612380ed04610f"}}
