{"type":"message","id":"21343bfb","parentId":"63d50746","timestamp":"2026-05-02T18:21:48.329Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Looking at the skill, step 7 in Gmail says \"Mark read: `gog gmail batch modify <msg_id> --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com --remove UNREAD`\" - so yes, the skill does mark emails as read after processing them.\n\nBut there's a nuance here - the skill processes NEW emails (within the 1-hour window). If it marks those as read, that's fine. But if an email from 2 hours ago is still unread and falls outside the current 1-hour window, it won't be processed and won't be marked as read.\n\nBobby might be asking because he wants ALL unread emails to be marked as read, not just the ones in the 1-hour window. Or he might just be confirming that the behavior is correct.\n","thinkingSignature":"876d7da024f886b6f724a46d8c0f447972d71491078737e44364efd57287240f"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nYes, the skill does mark each email as read after processing it:\n\n**Step 7 (Gmail):** `gog gmail batch modify <msg_id> --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com --remove UNREAD`\n\nSo any email that falls within the 1-hour window gets marked as read after it's reported.\n\n**One thing to note:** Emails outside the 1-hour window (like that 8-9 AM batch from this morning) won't be processed and won't be marked as read. They'll still sit in your unread inbox.\n\nIf you want ALL unread emails marked as read even if they're outside the 1-hour window, I can add a step to mark everything as read. But you'd only get alerted about the ones in the past hour. Want me to add that?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":111767,"output":316,"cacheRead":192,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":112275,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777746093338,"responseId":"064573ad685ec15328d7d749d60d05ae"}}
{"type":"message","id":"a67e72b0","parentId":"21343bfb","timestamp":"2026-05-02T18:23:14.229Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Okay so what I want you to do, go in my Gmail and tell me all unread emails and organize them and summarize them like you do during the Emmy email hourly check cron. This way for the hourly email check cron moving forward you can just tell me about all new unread emails. Is that easier?"}],"timestamp":1777746194225}}
