{"type":"custom_message","customType":"openclaw.runtime-context","content":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"chat_id\": \"telegram:8212808444\",\n  \"message_id\": \"2397\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"8212808444\",\n  \"sender\": \"B G\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-05-02 14:25 EDT\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"B G (8212808444)\",\n  \"id\": \"8212808444\",\n  \"name\": \"B G\"\n}\n```","display":false,"details":{"source":"openclaw-runtime-context"},"id":"aa3d4c4b","parentId":"b5942120","timestamp":"2026-05-02T18:25:31.054Z"}
{"type":"message","id":"3b9b456d","parentId":"aa3d4c4b","timestamp":"2026-05-02T18:26:02.464Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby wants to update the skill so that it only reports emails that are unread. This way, if he reads emails on his own, the cron won't re-report them since they'll already be marked as read. This is actually a good simplification.\n\nThe current skill logic:\n- Calculates \"1 hour ago from now\" as the window\n- Only shows emails received in that window\n- Marks them as read\n\nBobby wants:\n- Just check for unread emails (no time window)\n- If he reads them on his own, they won't be unread anymore so the cron won't report them\n- Simpler logic\n\nLet me update the skill to focus on unread emails and remove the time window complexity.\n","thinkingSignature":"4b007034ed89845973dc5a1fd90a0307fb0960e86cb522a49f331fd715d835e8"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_681krcpbanlr_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# Email Processor Skill\n\nCheck Gmail and iCloud for new unread emails, read full content, label properly, and send clean Telegram reports.\n\n---\n\n## CATEGORIES (use one per email)\n\n- 🔴 Bills/Payments — bills, due dates, bank alerts, money owed\n- 🟡 Orders — shipping, receipts, order updates, confirmations\n- 🔵 Updates — security alerts, account changes, service notices\n- ⚪ Low Priority — newsletters, promos, marketing, social\n\n---\n\n## GMAIL STEPS\n\n1. Search all unread inbox emails: `gog gmail search \"is:unread in:inbox\" --max 50 --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com`\n2. For each email found — read full body: `gog gmail get <msg_id> --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com`\n3. Label by category above\n4. Mark read: `gog gmail batch modify <msg_id> --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com --remove UNREAD`\n5. Send Gmail report to 8212808444 (MUST be a separate message from iCloud report)\n\n## GMAIL MESSAGE FORMAT (send as ONE message to 8212808444)\n```\n📬 GMAIL — X new email(s)\n\n🔴 URGENT:\n• [Sender] — [Subject] —> [Label]\n  └ [1-line snippet from email body]\n\n🟡 IMPORTANT:\n• [Sender] — [Subject] —> [Label]\n  └ [1-line snippet]\n\n⚪ LOW PRIORITY:\n• [Sender] — [Subject] —> [Label]\n  └ [1-line snippet]\n```\nIf no new: do NOT send any message (skip silently)\n\n---\n\n## ICLOUD STEPS\n\n1. Get credentials: `ICLOUD_CREDS=$(security find-generic-password -a \"rtg.bobby@icloud.com\" -s \"emmy-icloud-email\" -w 2>/dev/null)`\n2. Search unseen: `curl -s --url \"imaps://imap.mail.me.com/INBOX\" --user \"rtg.bobby@icloud.com:$ICLOUD_CREDS\" -X \"SEARCH UNSEEN\" 2>&1`\n3. Get checkpoint: `cat ~/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_icloud_email_id.txt` (use 0 if missing)\n4. Only process msg_num > checkpoint\n5. Fetch envelope: `curl -s --url \"imaps://imap.mail.me.com/INBOX\" --user \"rtg.bobby@icloud.com:$ICLOUD_CREDS\" -X \"FETCH <msg_num>:* (ENVELOPE)\" 2>&1`\n6. For each new message, label by urgency (no category label needed — just sender/subject/snippet)\n7. Update checkpoint: `echo <highest_msg_num> > ~/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_icloud_email_id.txt`\n8. Send iCloud report to 8212808444 (MUST be a separate message from Gmail report)\n\n## ICLOUD MESSAGE FORMAT (send as ONE message to 8212808444, AFTER Gmail message)\n```\n📬 ICLOUD — X new email(s)\n\n🔴 URGENT:\n• [Sender] — [Subject]\n  └ [1-line snippet]\n\n🟡 IMPORTANT:\n• [Sender] — [Subject]\n  └ [1-line snippet]\n\n⚪ LOW PRIORITY:\n• [Sender] — [Subject]\n  └ [1-line snippet]\n```\nIf no new: do NOT send any message (skip silently)\n\n---\n\n## CRITICAL RULES\n- Gmail AND iCloud reports MUST be sent as TWO SEPARATE Telegram messages\n- Send Gmail report FIRST, then iCloud report immediately after\n- Only report emails that are UNREAD — if you read an email on your own, it won't be reported since it's no longer unread\n- Read FULL email body for classification — not just headers\n- Categorize by email CONTENT and INTENT, not just sender name\n- If unsure about a category, pick the closest match and move on\n- If no new emails for an account, do NOT send any message for that account","path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/skills/email-processor/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":109825,"output":1052,"cacheRead":11264,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":122141,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777746331054,"responseId":"0645749b258c866ed25aea27306818dd"}}
