{"type":"message","id":"5088f5b2","parentId":"dd3d1a9a","timestamp":"2026-05-02T18:26:11.470Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Done. Updated the skill to:\n1. Check all unread emails (removed the timestamp-based filtering)\n2. Mark each as read after processing\n3. Only send messages if there are new unread emails\n4. No timestamp file needed for Gmail anymore\n5. iCloud still uses checkpoint but based on msg_num rather than time\n\nThe \"skip silently\" rule is already there - no message if no new emails.\n","thinkingSignature":"cf5387af157adf9b569ae123d054c642a1743733936874d8f9f2b34a07faf5b5"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\nDone! Updated the skill:\n\n✅ **Check all unread emails** — no timestamp filtering, just whatever is unread\n✅ **Mark as read** after processing each one\n✅ **Only report if there are new unread emails** — if you read something on your own, it won't be re-reported\n✅ **iCloud checkpoint** still tracks by msg_num (new emails only)\n✅ **Silent skip** — if no new emails for either account, no message sent\n\nThis is simpler and more intuitive. If you read emails on your own, the cron won't report them since they're no longer unread. The hourly cron will just pick up whatever new unread emails have accumulated since the last run."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1017,"output":225,"cacheRead":121024,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":122266,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777746362542,"responseId":"064574baf717abfd7d2aa46cccf2c5b7"}}
