{"type":"compaction","id":"9e043f09","parentId":"dce636ae","timestamp":"2026-05-02T18:39:59.589Z","summary":"\n\n## Goal\nFix Emmy Email Check cron job timeout issues, update email-processor skill to handle both Gmail and iCloud accounts, and verify Telegram message delivery works correctly.\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- Cron jobs hitting model idle timeout at ~4.5–5 minutes\n- Email skill must handle Gmail AND iCloud accounts\n- iCloud messages must use urgent/important/low priority format (same as Gmail)\n- Provider `models.providers.minimax-portal.timeoutSeconds` is protected — cannot be modified via `config.patch`\n- Cron runs every 1 hour (3600000ms), isolated session\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Identified root cause: MiniMax provider has no `timeoutSeconds` configured; model idle timeout ~4.5–5 min hardcoded\n- [x] Restarted gateway to clear stuck state\n- [x] Fully rewrote email-processor skill to include iCloud IMAP handling\n- [x] Simplified skill from ~200 lines to ~50 lines (direct steps, fewer rules, more railroaded)\n- [x] Changed from 12 categories to 3 urgency tiers: 🔴 Urgent, 🟡 Important, ⚪ Low Priority\n- [x] Updated Emmy Email Check cron job to use skill instead of inline 13-step script\n- [x] Added `timeoutSeconds: 300` to cron job payload\n- [x] Added `lightContext: true` to cron payload (~140K input tokens vs ~330K previously)\n- [x] Gmail: full email body reading for classification accuracy\n- [x] iCloud: envelope-only (sender/subject only, no body fetch)\n- [x] Manual run found 2 new Gmail emails (TikTok, Clipp.com), 0 iCloud — sent Telegram messages\n- [x] Timestamp reset to `1777737494` (11:58 AM EDT) to catch all new emails\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] Verifying cron delivers 2 separate Telegram messages back-to-back (Gmail first, then iCloud)\n\n### Blocked\n- `gateway config.patch` refuses to modify `models.providers.minimax-portal.timeoutSeconds` — path is protected\n- Provider-level model idle timeout not configurable through standard config\n\n## Decisions\n- **Skill-first approach**: Lean skill file (~50 lines) with direct steps; model loads fewer tokens and executes faster, reducing timeout risk\n- **Cron job points to skill**: Message references skill file directly, not inline instructions\n- **3 urgency tiers instead of 12 categories**: 🔴 Urgent (bills/security), 🟡 Important (orders/updates), ⚪ Low Priority (promos/news)\n- **Gmail full body, iCloud envelope-only**: Gmail step 7 → iCloud step 8, separate Telegram messages to 8212808444\n- **lightContext: true**: Reduces workspace context loading significantly\n\n## Open TODOs\n- Monitor if cron messages actually arrive on Telegram (previous runs showed \"delivered: true\" but Bobby didn't receive them)\n- Investigate alternative way to set provider-level model idle timeout (protected path issue)\n- Consider switching email cron to Grok 4.1 Fast model if MiniMax continues timing out\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Bobby monitors cron over next few hours and reports back on Telegram delivery status\n2. Confirm that cron delivers 2 separate Telegram messages back-to-back\n3. Next scheduled run: `1777741094817`\n\n## Critical Context\n- Last successful run session: `259b0dfc-1b44-4cf7-b982-65e9a8a007a6`\n- Last email check was manually run — 2 new Gmail (TikTok, Clipp.com), 0 iCloud\n- iCloud checkpoint currently at: `10`\n\n## Exact identifiers\n- Cron job ID: `d64702cd-150d-4b69-95b9-d1250b289efb`\n- Weather cron job ID: `720739ac-4722-437b-8271-b7c1189c905c`\n- Agent ID: `emmy`\n- Session target: `isolated`\n- Model: `minimax-portal/MiniMax-M2.7`\n- Skill path: `/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/skills/email-processor/SKILL.md`\n- Gmail timestamp file: `/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_email_check.timestamp`\n- iCloud timestamp file: `/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_icloud_email_id.txt`\n- iCloud IMAP endpoint: `imaps://imap.mail.me.com/INBOX`\n- iCloud keychain item: `emmy-icloud-email`\n- iCloud account: `rtg.bobby@icloud.com`\n- Gmail account: `rtg.bobby@gmail.com`\n- Telegram target: `8212808444`\n- Current Gmail timestamp: `1777737494`\n- iCloud checkpoint: `10`\n- Last successful run session: `259b0dfc-1b44-4cf7-b982-65e9a8a007a6`\n- Next scheduled run: `1777741094817`\n\n## Pending user asks\n- Bobby asked: \"Okay now what does the Emmy email check cron job say?\" — currently displaying above\n- Bobby asked to trigger the actual cron job end-to-end to test it works\n- Bobby wants to verify 2 separate Telegram messages (one Gmail, one iCloud) are sent back-to-back\n- Bobby will monitor cron over next few hours and report back on delivery status\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n\n\n## Decisions\n- **Timestamp comparison bug identified**: The `gog gmail get` output returns a human-readable date string (e.g., \"Sat, 02 May 2026 13:13:00 +0000 (UTC)\") but the skill was comparing it against a Unix epoch integer. The model was not correctly filtering emails by timestamp, causing old emails to be re-reported.\n- **Fix implemented**: Rewrote the Gmail steps in SKILL.md to explicitly convert the date string to Unix epoch using a python3 command before comparison.\n\n## Open TODOs\n- Verify the next cron run (at 13:58 PM based on nextRunAtMs: 1777741094817) properly filters emails using the new timestamp comparison logic.\n\n## Constraints/Rules\n- Gmail and iCloud reports MUST be sent as TWO SEPARATE Telegram messages (Gmail first, then iCloud).\n- Always update timestamps AFTER sending both reports.\n- Only process emails where email-epoch > LAST_CHECK_EPOCH.\n\n## Pending user asks\n- (none)\n\n## Exact identifiers\n- Skill file: `/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/skills/email-processor/SKILL.md`\n- Gmail account: `rtg.bobby@gmail.com`\n- Timestamp file: `~/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_email_check.timestamp`\n- iCloud email: `rtg.bobby@icloud.com`\n- iCloud keychain item name: `emmy-icloud-email`\n- Telegram recipient ID: `8212808444`\n- Gmail message IDs: `19de8d22cfadb367