{"type":"message","id":"1e8f1636","parentId":"52bd6b36","timestamp":"2026-05-02T18:43:52.826Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Still showing 7 unread. But we just marked 3 as read. This seems like threads with multiple messages are not getting fully cleared.\n\nLet me try a different approach - maybe I need to remove the UNREAD label from the entire thread, not just the individual message. Let me check what \"batch modify\" does. Maybe it only marks the specific message, not the entire thread.\n\nActually, let me look at this differently. The issue is these are message threads. When a thread has messages, the search shows \"X msgs\" and if ANY message in the thread is unread, the whole thread shows up in the unread search.\n\nLet me check the actual messages in these threads to understand the structure better.\n\nActually, I think what might be happening is these are threads where there are multiple messages in the thread, some read some unread. The batch modify only affects the specific message ID.\n\nBut wait - I searched for `is:unread in:inbox` and it returned those specific message IDs. So those IDs should be the unread ones. When I mark them read, they should disappear from the unread search...\n\nUnless the issue is that the batch modify is failing silently for some of them, or there's some caching delay.\n\nLet me try one more time and then just move on. I'll mark them all again.\n","thinkingSignature":"742af04d7283ac021c8ed143f9f61f2f51f2521bf4683b5fc5e57ac4cd1b056b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ack6es9yt1d4_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"gog gmail batch modify 19ddfc93043ecfb8 19dcb207a2a65fac 19d97d544cad1971 19d97b7d79701d1d 19d77e2e55e7f7dd 19d73d8611945bc8 19d64418bfe6d633 --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com --remove UNREAD 2>&1 && sleep 3 && gog gmail search 'is:unread in:inbox' --max 200 --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com 2>&1 | grep \"^19\" | wc -l","timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provide