{"type":"message","id":"90a28c39","parentId":"aff1a2b9","timestamp":"2026-05-02T18:44:59.262Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Still showing. These are thread-based emails. The batch modify might be marking the thread as read, not the individual message. Let me check the thread structure more carefully. These show [8 msgs], [2 msgs] etc which means they're part of threads.\n\nActually wait - when I do `gog gmail batch modify <id> --remove UNREAD`, it's removing the UNREAD label from that message. But maybe these are being re-labeled because the thread has other unread messages in it?\n\nLet me check: maybe the issue is that these are threaded and removing UNREAD from one message doesn't remove it from the thread view? Or maybe there's some labeling rule that's re-applying UNREAD?\n\nActually, looking at the label output: `CATEGORY_UPDATES,INBOX` - there's no UNREAD label showing anymore. So they ARE marked as read! But the search is still returning them...\n\nMaybe gog's `is:unread` search isn't perfectly accurate in real-time? Let me try the actual gmail API directly to check.\n\nActually, let me try a different approach - let me check via the Gmail web API or just accept that there might be some lag and confirm what the actual UNREAD label state is via a different method.\n\nActually wait - look at the output format. The header says \"ID DATE FROM SUBJECT LABELS THREAD\". These are columns. Looking at the LABELS column for 19ddfc93043ecfb8: `CATEGORY_UPDATES,INBOX` - no UNREAD. So it IS marked as read. The issue might be that the search index hasn't updated yet, or there's some caching.\n\nLet me just verify with a direct API call or wait and check again.\n","thinkingSignature":"b0435ac98567a2fa04c5489dd622436339bb3e23765c21351ab4791fa590df6d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wkw4btfzifdt_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sleep 5 && gog gmail search 'is:unread in:inbox' --max 200 --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com 2